t%20change%20much%2C%20at%20least%20in%20the%20short%20term.%20%26quot%3BGiven%20the%20density%20of%20minefields%20close%20to%20Russia's%20first%20defensive%20lines%2C%20tanks%20such%20as%20the%20M1A1%20Abrams%20alongside%20other%20modern%20Western%20armor%20are%20restricted%20in%20their%20ability%20to%20play%20prominent%20roles%20in%20offensive%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20Yanchik%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20Ukraine%20is%20able%20to%20consolidate%20its%20position%20beyond%20Russia's%20initial%20line%20of%20defense%20however%2C%20these%20tanks%20will%20be%20integral%20in%20pushing%20into%20less%20heavily%20fortified%20areas.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20could%20be%20where%20the%20Abrams%20shines%20brightest.%20%26quot%3BNow%2C%20if%20the%20infantry%20makes%20a%20breakthrough%2C%26quot%3B%20Cancian%20told%20Insider%2C%20%26quot%3Bthen%20they%20might%20be%20able%20to%20open%20up%20enough%20of%20a%20gap%20that%20you%20can%20really%20push%20the%20tanks%20through%20and%20then%20use%20all%20of%20their%20capabilities.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20problem%20is%20Ukraine%20only%20has%2031%20Abrams%2C%20a%20small%20fraction%20of%20its%20entire%20tank%20force%2C%20which%20includes%20other%20Western%20armor%20such%20as%20UK-provided%20Leopard%20and%20Germany's%20Challenger%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Soviet-era%20tanks%2C%20which%20are%20the%20bulk%20of%20their%20forces.%C2%A0And%20maintaining%20the%20Abrams%20%E2%80%94%20taking%20care%20of%20its%20%3Cs%3Eincredibly%3C%2Fs%3E%20powerful%20but%20needy%20engine%2C%20which%20has%20sometimes%20been%20referred%20to%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bjet%20engine%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20keeping%20spare%20parts%20and%20fuel%20readily%20available%20%E2%80%94%20will%20also%20limit%20how%20and%20when%20the%20Abrams%20is%20used.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225739%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20Marines%20prepare%20their%20M1%20Abrams%20tank%20to%20take%20part%20in%20an%20exercise%20to%20capture%20an%20airfield%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Trident%20Juncture%202018%2C%20a%20NATO-led%20military%20exercise%2C%20on%20November%201%2C%202018%2C%20near%20the%20town%20of%20Oppdal%2C%20Norway.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653a547096f7540cd066407d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223826%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Marines%20prepare%20their%20M1%20Abrams%20tank%20to%20take%20part%20in%20an%20exercise%20to%20capture%20an%20airfield%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Trident%20Juncture%202018%2C%20a%20NATO-led%20military%20exercise%2C%20on%20November%201%2C%202018%2C%20near%20the%20town%20of%20Oppdal%2C%20Norway.%3Cp%3EJONATHAN%20NACKSTRAND%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20winter%20on%20the%20horizon%2C%20and%20potential%20for%20a%20Russian%20offensive%2C%20Ukraine%20will%20also%20have%20to%20decide%20the%20best%20role%20for%20the%20Abrams%20in%20the%20longer%20term.%20Zelenskyy%20has%20vowed%20troops%20will%20continue%20to%20push%20against%20Russian%20defenses%20throughout%20a%20wet%20autumn%20and%20cold%20winter%2C%20although%20it%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20if%20weather%20will%20slow%20down%20offensive%20movement%20as%20it%20did%20last%20year.%20Right%20now%2C%20it%20appears%20as%20though%20there%20could%20be%20two%20options%3A%20employing%20the%20Abrams%20this%20winter%20to%20bolster%20the%20fighting%2C%20or%20reserve%20them%20for%20a%C2%A0counteroffensive%20next%20spring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can%20see%20both%20approaches%2C%26quot%3B%20Cancian%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20links%20to%20a%20much%20broader%20question%2C%20which%20is%20Ukraine's%20theory%20of%20victory%2C%20and%20how%20are%20they%20going%20to%20win%20this%20war%3F%26quot%3B%20He%20added%20that%20with%20the%20counteroffensive%20bogged%20down%2C%20Ukraine%20could%20either%20%26quot%3Bkeep%20grinding%20away%20through%20the%20winter%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bwait%2C%20build%20their%20strength%2C%20and%20launch%20a%20new%20cou