ent%20of%20baby%20boomers%20is%20one%20long-term%20challenge%20employers%20are%20up%20against.%20The%20labor%20force%20participation%20rate%20for%20those%2055%20years%20old%20and%20over%20continued%20to%20be%20below%20where%20it%20was%20before%20the%20pandemic%20as%20of%20September%2C%20based%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FLNS11324230%5C%22%3EBureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20data%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20many%20fields%2C%20labor%20shortages%20are%20going%20to%20get%20worse%2C%20not%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20Pollak%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20there's%20a%20lot%20that%20employers%20can%20do%2C%20boosting%20pay%20and%20benefits%2C%20offering%20more%20flexibility%2C%20advertising%20at%20job%20postings%20better%2C%20there's%20only%20so%20much%20they%20can%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Pollak%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20many%20structural%20barriers%20that%20they're%20coming%20up%20against.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20boosting%20pay%20could%20be%20one%20thing%20employers%20can%20do%20to%20attract%20new%20workers%2C%20US%20inflation%20has%20also%20been%20too%20high.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-economic-outlook-cpi-consumer-price-index-september-data-report-2023-10%5C%22%3EInflation%20has%20been%20cooling%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20greater%20than%20the%20Fed's%202%25%20target.%C2%A0But%20a%20bit%20of%20tightness%20in%20parts%20of%20the%20labor%20market%20probably%20won't%20make%20inflation%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20easy%20to%20think%20that%20the%20sectors%20that%20face%20long-term%20labor%20shortages%20also%20face%20rapidly%20increasing%20wages%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that%20isn't%20always%20the%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20Terrazas%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20sectors%20with%20enduring%20labor%20shortages%2C%20businesses%20face%20a%20limited%20capacity%20to%20pass%20along%20cost%20increases%20to%20their%20customers%20%E2%80%94%20which%20means%20that%20they%20are%20unable%20to%20increase%20wages%20as%20quickly%20as%20they%20would%20like%20in%20order%20to%20attract%20new%20workers%20to%20the%20field.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20ways%20to%20address%20long-term%20shortages.%20Terrazas%20said%20demand%20for%20more%20technology%20usage%20or%20immigrants%20are%20responses%20seen%20in%20industries%20with%20this%20problem.%20Another%20is%20relaxing%20skills%20needed%20for%20a%20job%20or%20the%20credentials%20and%20licensing%20needed%2C%20as%20these%20can%20be%20barriers%20for%20job%20entry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%20economist%20Cory%20Stahle%C2%A0pointed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-is-there-labor-shortage-employers-overlooking-talent-hiring-jobs-2022-6%5C%22%3Eoverlooked%20talent%20pools%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20way%20to%20address%20labor%20shortages.%20That%20may%20include%20workers%20with%20disabilities%20as%20well%20as%20second%20chance%20workers%2C%20or%20people%20reentering%20the%20workforce%20after%20incarceration%20and%20those%20with%20criminal%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20Stahle%20also%20mentioned%20%26quot%3Bproductivity%20enhancing%20technology%20like%20AI%26quot%3B%20could%20also%20help%2C%20he%20noted%20based%20on%20Indeed%20research%20there%20are%20jobs%20where%20generative%20AI%20might%20not%20be%20able%20to%20do%20too%20much%2C%20such%20as%20in-person%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBelow%20are%20some%20of%20the%20kinds%20of%20work%20and%20industries%20where%20there%20may%20be%20labor%20shortages%C2%A0long%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHealthcare%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221776%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Medical%20professional%2C%20nurse%2C%20or%20doctor%20sitting%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653983c8356802a56be43521%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221332%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHealthcare%20is%20one%20industry%20that%20may%20have%20long-term%20labor%20shortages.%3Cp%3EER%20Productions%20Limited%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHealthcare%20is%20one%20industry%20Stahle%20sees%20long-term%20labor%20shortages%20continuing%20to%20be%20an%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20see%20the%20nursing%20shortage%20story%20has%20been%20a%20multi-year%20story%20at%20this%20point%2C%20and%20we%20continue%20to%20see%20nurses%20saying%20that%20they%20want%20to%20leave%2C%20they're%20burned%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Stahle%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncsbn.org%2Fnews%2Fncsbn-research-projects-significant-nursing-workforce-shortages-and-crisis%5C%22%3ENational%20Council%20of%20State%20Boards%20of%20Nursing%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0found%20that%20many%20registered%20nurses%20already%20exited%20or%20want%20to%20leave%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BApproximately%20100%2C000%20registered%20nurses%20(RNs)%20left%20the%20workforce%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20in%20the%20past%20two%20years%20due%20to%20stress%2C%20burnout%20and%20retirements%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20April%20news%20release%20from%20the%20National%20Council%20of%20State%20Boards%20of%20Nursing%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnother%20610%2C388%20RNs%20reported%20an%20'intent%20to%20leave'%20the%20workforce%20by%202027%20due%20to%20stress%2C%20burnout%20and%20retirement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20an%20aging%20population%20will%20mean%20more%20demand%20for%20healthcare%20workers%2C%20including%20in%20healthcare%20support%20jobs.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Femp%2Ftables%2Foccupations-most-job-growth.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProjection%20data%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20home%20health%20and%20personal%20care%20aides%20are%20projected%20to%20see%20growth%20of%20804%2C600%20from%202022%20to%202032%2C%20the%20most%20of%20any%20job%20tracked%20by%20BLS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHealthcare%20is%20a%20