aid%20%26quot%3Bmy%20salary%20is%20too%20low%2C%26quot%3B%2070%25%20of%20these%20teachers%20considering%20this%20said%20%26quot%3Bthe%20stress%20and%20disappointments%20of%20teaching%20aren't%20worth%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETeachers%20also%20may%20have%20to%20take%20into%20account%20their%20spending%20budget%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fschool-classroom-spending-teacher-why-spend-own-money-2023-10%5C%22%3Ehow%20much%20they%20may%20have%20to%20spend%20out%20of%20pocket%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20lesson%20plans%2C%20supplies%20for%20students%2C%20books%2C%20and%20other%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20ask%20other%20professions%20to%20try%20to%20do%20their%20job%20without%20the%20materials%20they%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20teacher%2C%20who%20shared%20with%20Insider%20some%20of%20the%20items%20she%20has%20had%20to%20buy%20over%20the%20years%20for%20her%20classroom%20like%20some%20books%20and%20bins%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20a%20lot%20of%20teachers%20are%20expected%20to%20do%20their%20job%20without%20materials%20that%20they%20have%20or%20that%20they%20need.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20older%20teachers%20may%20be%20deciding%20it's%20time%20to%20retire%2C%20Nela%20Richardson%2C%20chief%20economist%20of%20ADP%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Byounger%20teachers%20are%20not%20flowing%20into%20that%20profession%20as%20much%2C%20and%20they're%20leaving.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESkilled%20trades%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221776%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Construction%20workers%20at%20a%20construction%20site%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653a6d170487ff031caf097c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221332%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3Eskynesher%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETerrazas%20said%20there%20are%20cyclical%20shortages%20in%20construction%20when%20it%20is%20booming.%20Otherwise%2C%20there%20can%20be%20shortages%20in%20skilled%20trades%2C%20such%20as%20plumbing%2C%20given%20the%20skills%20and%20training%20needed%20for%20this%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20some%20communities%2C%20they%20are%20also%20unionized%2C%20which%20also%20can%20limit%20access%20to%20apprenticeships%20and%20training%20opportunities%2C%26quot%3B%20Terrazas%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20there's%20no%20doubt%20that%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20those%20skilled%20vocational%20trades%20in%20construction%2C%20some%20of%20those%20areas%20find%20shortages.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERichardson%20said%20labor%20and%20skill%20shortages%20are%20prominent%20reasons%20behind%20the%20lack%20of%20housing%20inventory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20think%20about%20the%20construction%20industry%2C%20it%20is%20a%20telltale%20sign%20to%20other%20industries%20about%20what%20happens%20when%20there's%20not%20a%20good%20skilled%20workforce%20to%20replace%20people%20who%20are%20retiring%20in%20that%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20Richardson%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20could%20foreshadow%20labor%20shortages%20over%20the%20next%2010%20years%20as%20more%20boomers%20leave%20these%20industries%20and%20young%20people%20do%20not%20follow%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20help%20attract%20workers%20in%20construction%20and%20elsewhere%2C%20Richardson%20said%20working%20on%20addressing%20gender%20pay%20gaps%20and%20%26quot%3Bwidening%20the%20pipeline%20through%20education%20and%20training%26quot%3B%20as%20two%20things%20that%20could%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDaycare%20and%20childcare%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221798%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20teacher%20and%20a%20student%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653a6e0196f7540cd06652f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221346%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBilly%20Hustace%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20child%20care%20industry%20has%20long%20faced%20challenges%20in%20finding%20sufficient%20workers%20despite%20relatively%20low%20education%20and%20training%20barriers%20to%20entry%2C%26quot%3B%20Terrazas%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Femp%2Ftables%2Feducation-and-training-by-occupation.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBLS%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20childcare%20workers%20typically%20need%20a%20high%20school%20diploma%20or%20equivalent%20for%20entry.%20Terrazas%20noted%20the%20problem%20finding%20childcare%20workers%20is%20heavily%20due%20to%20%26quot%3Bthe%20physically%20intensive%20nature%20of%20the%20work%26quot%3B%20and%20can%20also%20be%20due%20to%20%26quot%3Bthe%20inability%20to%20pass%20along%20the%20full%20cost%20of%20labor%20to%20customers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECenter-%20and%20home-based%20childcare%20can%20cost%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20annually%2C%20based%20on%20price%20data%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.dol.gov%2F2023%2F01%2F24%2Fnew-childcare-data-shows-prices-are-untenable-for-families%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enoted%20in%20a%20blog%20post%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20no%20easy%20solutions%20to%20the%20childcare%20workforce%20challenge%2C%20particularly%20in%20communities%20where%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20is%20high%2C%26quot%3B%20Terrazas%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fooh%2Fpersonal-care-and-service%2Fchildcare-workers.htm%23tab-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOccupational%20Outlook%20Handbook%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20noted%20that%20although%20employment%20for%20childcare%20workers%20is%20projected%20to%20fall%20from%202022%20to%202032%2C%20there%20will%20be%20job%20openings%20each%20year.%20The%20BLS%20website%20stated%20%26quot%3Babout%20153%2C100%20openings%20for%20childcare%20workers%20are%20projected%20each%20year%2C%20on%20average%2C%20over%20the%20decade.%20All%20of%20those%20openings%20are%20expected%20to%20result%20from%20the%20need%20to%20replace%20workers%20who%20transfer%20to%20other%20occupations%20or%20exit%20the%20labor%20force%2C%20such%20as%20to%20retire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pay%20for%20workers%20in%20this%20industry%20could%20also%20add%20to%20the%20problem.%20Stahle%20said%20based%20on%20Indeed%20Wage%20Tracker%20data%20that%20childcare%20jobs%20usually%20note%20low%20pay%20in%20their%20open%20positions%20compared%20to%20other%20roles%20posted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20years%20now%2C%20the%20supply%20of%20childcare%20services%20has%20struggled%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20parents'%20demands%2C%26quot%3B%20Stahle%20said.%20%26quot%3BTo%20catch%20up%20to%20that%20would%20require%20finding%20even%20more%20workers%20in%20a%20sector%20that%20is%20already%20facing%20hiring%20challenges.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETourism%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221778%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Family%20playing%20in%20snow%20at%20a%20ski%20resort%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653a6e6596f7540cd0665408%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Milchev%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FUSLAH%230%5C%22%3ELeisure%20and%20hospitality%3C%2Fa%3E%20finally%20isn't%20too%20far%20off%20from%20being%20back%20at%20pre-pandemic%20employment.%20Meanwhile%2C%20there%20are%20parts%20of%20the%20sector%20where%20worker%20demand%20issues%C2%A0seem%20to%20be%20common.%20Terrazas%20pointed%20to%20resort%20towns%2C%20like%20beaches%20or%20ski%20places%2C%20where%20they%20may%20have%20to%20bring%20workers%20to%20these%20places%20a%20few%20months%20each%20year%20to%20meet%20this%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20tend%20to%20be%20young%20workers%2C%20they%20tend%20to%20be%20immigrant%20workers%20who%20could%20go%20into%20those%20seasonal%20resort%20towns%20and%20do%20all%20the%20services%20that%20vacationers%20require%20%E2%80%94%20from%20cooking%20to%20food%20service%2C%20to%20cleaning%20rooms%2C%20to%20teaching%20ski%20lessons%20or%20teaching%20surfing%20lessons%2C%26quot%3B%20Terrazas%20said%2C%20adding%20these%20occupations%20%26quot%3Btend%20to%20have%20long-term%20shortages.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EFarming%20and%20mining%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221778%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Farmer%20looking%20at%20a%20field%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653a6ec6356802a56be486f3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESteve%20Smith%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20industry%20where%20this%20problem%20may%20be%20prevalent%20long%20term%20is%20in%20natural%20resources%20extraction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETerrazas%20noted%20these%20jobs%20in%20mining%2C%20logging%2C%20and%20oil%20work%20can%20require%20%26quot%3Bbig%20lifestyle%20sacrifices.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20not%20only%20can%20these%20jobs%20mean%20working%20long%20hours%20but%20they%20can%20include%20working%20outside%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bcan%20be%20personally%20risky%20if%20you're%20working%20with%20large%20heavy%20machinery.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20they%20can%20be%20considered%20%26quot%3Bdirty%2C%20dangerous%2C%20and%20demanding%26quot%3B%20jobs%2C%20per%20Terrazas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgricultural%20work%20is%20another%20field%20where%20Terrazas%20said%20there%20are%20often%20long-term%20labor%20shortages.%20That's%20because%20people%20may%20be%20spending%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20outside%20in%20a%20physically%20demanding%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20world%20where%20we%20know%20temperatures%20are%20rising%2C%20it%20is%20very%20difficult%2C%20potentially%20physically%20dangerous%20work%20to%20be%20tending%20crops%20or%20picking%20crops%20in%20peak%20harvest%20season%20or%20in%20summer%2C%26quot%3B%20Terrazas%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERetail%2C%20restaurants%2C%20and%20other%20industries%20that%20employ%20young%20people%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221777%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20making%20a%20purchase%20at%20a%20store%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653a6f1c96f7540cd066550d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMoMo%20Productions%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStahle%20also%20noted%20to%20Insider%20%26quot%3Bindustries%20that%20are%20typically%20staffed%20by%20younger%20workers%26quot%3B%20like%20retail%20as%20another%20kind%20of%20industry%20that%20may%20be%20affected%20by%20long-term%20labor%20shortages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20the%20population%20growth%20rate%20has%20slowed%20down%2C%20if%20that%20trend%20continues%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20see%20that%20some%20sectors%20like%20food%20service%20and%20sales%20and%20retail%20and%20these%20kind%20of%20industries%20that%20typically%20depend%20on%20younger%20workers%20are%20really%20going%20to%20have%20to%20adapt%20and%20maybe%20change%20the%20way%20that%20they%20approach%20things%2C%20or%20they're%20going%20to%20also%20be%20facing%20those%20type%20of%20labor%20shortages%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Stahle%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOccupational%20data%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fcps%2Fcpsaat11b.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%202022%20shows%20the%20median%20age%20for%20waiters%20and%20waitresses%20was%2026%2C%20around%2022%20for%20fast%20food%20and%20counter%20workers%2C%20and%20around%2026%20for%20cashiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteacher-shortage-schools-