g%20is%20untouched.%20The%20school%20is%20damaged%3B%20the%20church%20is%20damaged%2C%20everything%20has%20been%20hit%3B%20the%20bus%20station%20is%20damaged%3B%20it%20just%20goes%20on%20and%20on%20and%20on.%20The%20military-civilian%20authority%20showed%20me%20around%20and%20he%20showed%20us%20his%20house.%20His%20house%20had%20been%20destroyed.%20He%20went%20to%20work%20an%20hour%20before%20the%20Russians%20attacked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20went%20into%20a%20shelter%20in%20Orikhiv%20and%20it%20was%20in%20one%20of%20these%20old%20Soviet%20residential%20buildings%2C%20went%20into%20the%20basement%20and%20there's%20a%20bunch%20of%20old%20people.%20They're%20in%20the%20basement%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20they're%20dank%2C%20they're%20windowless%2C%20they%20have%20no%20running%20water%2C%20no%20toilets%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20elderly%20people%20are%20living%20in%20these%20places%2C%20and%20they%20padlock%20them.%20They%20have%20twin%20beds.%20They%20have%20just%20a%20teapot%20and%20some%20of%20their%20cooking%20supplies%20and%20bags%20on%20the%20walls%20and%20some%20of%20their%20clothing.%20And%20I%20asked%20the%20people%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20do%20you%20do%20during%20the%20day%3F%20Where%20do%20you%20spend%20your%20time%3F%26quot%3B%20And%20they%20mostly%20spend%20their%20time%20in%20the%20shelters.%20They%20have%20sort%20of%20a%20communal%20area%20too%2C%20where%20you%20can%20sit%20at%20a%20table%2C%20and%20you%20can%20chat.%20But%20they%20also%20do%20go%20home.%20They%20do%20their%20laundry%20at%20home%2C%20they%20bathe%20at%20home%2C%20and%20some%20of%20them%20work%20on%20their%20gardens%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20really%20dismal%20place%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20nothing%20left%20in%20this%20village%2C%20but%20the%20Russians%20continue%20to%20shell%20it%20because%20there's%2015%2C000%20Ukrainian%20troops%20there.%20And%20it's%20hard%20to%20tell%20where%20the%20Ukrainian%20troops%20are.%20It%20looks%20like%20it's%20a%20hollowed-out%2C%20nearly%20destroyed%20building%2C%20but%20then%20you%20get%20close%20to%20the%20building%2C%20and%20you'll%20hear%20the%20hum%20of%20a%20generator%2C%20and%20you'll%20see%20graffiti%20that%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BWarning%2FDanger.%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%2C%20go%20away.%26quot%3B%20And%20the%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20are%20in%20the%20basement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22grimy%20basement%20featuring%20bed%20and%20personal%20items%20along%20the%20wall%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653970ed356802a56be40119%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMost%20of%20the%20civilians%20still%20remaining%20in%20Orikhiv%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20are%20elderly%20and%20spend%20much%20of%20their%20time%20sheltering%20in%20basements.%3Cp%3EMelinda%20Haring%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERegarding%20the%20older%20civilians%20who%20have%20stayed%20behind%2C%20the%20obvious%20question%20is%3A%20%26quot%3BWhy%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20get%20a%20mix%20of%20answers.%20For%20some%2C%20it's%20too%20expensive%20to%20move.%20There's%20not%20enough%20housing%20in%20Zaporizhzhia%2C%20which%20is%20the%20nearest%2C%20closest%20safe%20city.%20They%20don't%20feel%20comfortable%20there.%20They're%20afraid%20that%20someone%20will%20loot%20their%20house.%20And%20then%20there's%20probably%20a%20small%20percentage%20of%20them%20that%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0no%20one's%20going%20to%20admit%20this%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that%20have%20pro-Russian%20sympathy%20and%20want%20the%20Russians%20to%20move%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20older%20and%20infirm%20people.%20These%20are%20people%20in%20their%2070s%20and%2080s%20and%20their%20lives%20are%20there.%20There's%20a%20city%20well%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20one%20well%20in%20Orikhiv%20that%20works.%20I%20was%20there%20on%20a%20Saturday%20morning.%20We%20figured%20that%20the%20Russians%20were%20too%20lazy%20to%20shell%20early%20on%20Saturday%20morning%3B%20that%20they%20were%20still%20hungover%20from%20the%20night%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22woman%20in%20helmet%20and%20flak%20jacket%20standing%20with%20two%20men%20and%20a%20dog%20in%20a%20field%2C%20looking%20at%20the%20ground%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65396f51356802a56be3fc09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMykola%C2%A0Vinnichenko%2C%20head%20of%C2%A0the%C2%A0Orikhiv%C2%A0military%20administration%2C%20inspects%20the%20city%20well%20that%20provides%201%2C200%20remaining%20civilians%20with%20fresh%20drinking%20water.%20Two%20people%20were%20recently%20killed%20at%20the%20well.%3Cp%3EAndrey%20Liscovich%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20there%20from%207%3A30%20a.m.%20to%209%3A30%20a.m.%20and%20the%20well%20that%20we%20went%20to%20wasn't%20working.%20It%20was%20having%20mechanical%20problems.%20People%20have%20to%20go%20there%20and%20hand%20pump%20their%20water.%20They%20bring%20their%20bikes.%20I%20saw%20a%20guy%2C%20he%20brought%20his%20bike.%20He%20has%20a%20container%20of%20water%20that%20he%20fills.%20He%20puts%20it%20back%20on%20his%20bike%20and%20then%20rides%20his%20bike%20home%20to%20this%20completely%20bombed-out%20village.%20And%20that's%20how%20he%20gets%20his%20fresh%20water.%20Two%20people%20were%20killed%20there%20two%20days%20prior%20to%20us%20being%20there%2C%20but%20that's%20one%20of%20the%20only%20lifelines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20three%20stores%20that%20remain%20open%20and%20the%20bestsellers%20are%20all%20stimulants.%20It's%20coffee%2C%20cigarettes%2C%20and%20chocolate.%20Those%20are%20the%20three%20bestsellers%20at%20the%20stores.%20And%20there's%20a%20market%2C%20and%20the%20market%20has%20great%2C%20beautiful%20fresh%20produce.%20And%20there%20were%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20chit-chatting%20with%20the%20older%20ladies%20there%20buying%20food.%20And%20there's%20dogs.%20And%20it's%20probably%20the%20most%20joyful%20place%20in%20this%20little%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22convenience%20store%20featuring%20shelves%20full%20of%20instant%20coffee.%20forefront%20includes%20smaller%20instant%20coffee%20packets%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653970560487ff031cae7bc1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECoffee%20and%20snacks%20are%20available%20for%20sale%20at%20one%20of%20the%20few%20stores%20still%20open%20in%20Orikhiv%2C%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EMelinda%20Haring%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20morale%20among%20the%20civilian%20and%20military%20population%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20really%20interesting%20conversations.%20I%20spoke%20with%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20in%20Zaporizhzhia.%C2%A0I%20spoke%20with%20a%20bunch%20of%20people.%20They're%20flinty%20and%20steely%20and%20determined.%20But%20when%20you%20talk%20to%20them%20for%20more%20than%20five%20minutes%2C%20they'll%20tell%20you%20that%20there's%20frustration%20that%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20haven't%20been%20rotated%20out.%20The%20same%20set%20of%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20that's%20been%20serving%20has%20been%20serving%20for%20more%20than%20600%20days.%20They%20only%20get%2030%20days%20off%20a%20year%20and%20those%2030%20days%20are%20not%20contiguous%2C%20you%20can%20only%20take%2010%20at%20a%20time.%20So%20they%20haven't%20seen%20much%20of%20their%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20a%20lot%20of%20them%20feel%20like%20there's%20not%20a%20whole-of-society%20effort%20behind%20them.%20There's%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20are%20in%20Kyiv%20posing%20for%20selfies%20and%20eating%20in%20restaurants%2C%20while%20a%20small%20segment%20of%20Ukrainian%20society%20is%20the%20one%20that's%20sticking%20its%20neck%20out.%20That's%20a%20common%20feeling.%20There's%20a%20lot%20of%20stories%20of%20divorce%20and%20of%20family%20separation%20and%20also%20depression.%20And%20a%20lot%20of%20PTSD.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDid%20any%20of%20the%20soldiers%20that%20you%20spoke%20to%20discuss%20what%20they%20want%2C%20either%20from%20their%20own%20government%20or%20from%20the%20American%20government%3F%20Just%20in%20general%2C%20what%20are%20their%20needs%20on%20the%20frontlines%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20depends.%20The%20medic%20that%20I%20spoke%20to%20said%20they%20need%20more%20armored%20cars.%20He%20does%20not%20have%20enough%20armored%20cars%20to%20get%20his%20guys%20out%2C%20and%20it's%20an%20acute%20need.%20And%20so%20he%20has%20people%20bleed%20out%20because%20he%20can't%20evacuate%20them%20to%20a%20hospital.%20It's%20particularly%20bad%20in%20the%20summer.%20It's%20less%20bad%20in%20the%20winter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJune%20and%20July%20are%20hard%20months%20because%20there's%20just%20a%20lot%20more%20light.%20There's%20a%20need%20for%20tourniquets.%20There's%20a%20need%20for%20cars.%20I%20went%20to%20an%20NGO%20in%20Zaporizhzhia%20and%20they%20need%20vehicles%20to%20deliver%20aid%20supplies%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Ukrainians%20in%20general.%20I%20also%20went%20to%20a%20drone%20school%20and%20I%20saw%20pilots%20learning%20how%20to%20become%20pilots.%20I%20got%20to%20fly%20a%20drone.%20I%20got%20to%20see%20a%20bunch%20of%20drones.%20And%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20pieces%20are%20poor%20quality.%20They're%20shoddy%2C%20they're%20made%20in%20Chinese%20factories%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20attention%20to%20detail.%20They're%20missing%20pieces.%20They're%20broken%20when%20they%20arrive.%20The%20Ukrainians%20are%20way%20behind%20the%20Russians%20on%20drones%2C%20and%20this%20is%20the%20future%20of%20the%20war.%20Ukraine%20doesn't%20have%20enough%20drone%20pilots%20and%20they%20don't%20have%20enough%20sophisticated%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22street%20with%20potholes%2C%20and%20burnt%20trees%20and%20electric%20poles%20over%20a%20destroyed%20yellow%20structure%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653974750487ff031cae88ae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhat's%20left%20of%20the%20bus%20stop%20in%20Orikhiv%2C%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EMelinda%20Haring%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThese%20are%20surveillance%20drones%20used%20for%20artillery%20spotting%20and%20stuff%20like%20that%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20two%20major%20categories%20of%20drones.%20There's%20the%20surveillance%20drones%2C%20and%20then%20there's%20the%20attack%20drones%3B%20the%20surveillance%20drones%20are%20bigger%2C%20and%20the%20attack%20drones%20are%20smaller.%20I%20saw%20both%20of%20those%2C%20and%20some%20of%20them%20are%20used%20for%20spotting.%20The%20kamikaze%20drones%20are%20used%20to%20drop%20bombs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20you%20were%20not%20terribly%20impressed%3F%20Because%20my%20sense%20was%20that%20maybe%20it%20was%20the%20Russians%20that%20were%20struggling%20with%20drone%20technology%20%E2%80%94%20that%20they%20were%20the%20ones%20trying%20to%20catch%20up%20after%20the%20war%20started.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%2C%20other%20way%20around.%20The%20Russians%20are%20really%2C%20really%20good%20at%20this%2C%20and%20they%20poured%20a%20lot%20of%20technology%20and%20resources%20into%20this.%20They're%20ahead%20of%20the%20Ukrainians.%20The%20Ukrainians%20are%20trying%20to%20catch%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20the%20disappointing%20part%20to%20me%20is%20that%20the%20Ukrainian%20government%20has%20made%20a%20big%20deal%20out%20of%20this.%20And%20when%20you%20talk%20to%20a%20local%20activist%20and%20people%20who%20are%20trying%20to%20fill%20this%20need%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20they'll%20say%20that%20the%20government%20effort%20is%20not%20enough%2C%20and%20that%20the%20subsidies%20that%20the%20government%20has%20committed%20is%20not%20enough.%20And%20that's%20why%2C%20of%20course%2C%20Ukrainian%20civil%20society%20is%20jumping%20into%20the%20gap%2C%20again%2C%20and%20it's%20training%20drone%20pilots%20and%20buying%20drones%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20common%20theme%20of%20Ukrainian%20politics.%20It%20doesn't%20matter%20the%20sector%2C%20where%20there's%20state%20failure%2C%20Ukrainian%20civil%20society%20fixes%20it%E2%80%A6.%20When%20you%20speak%20with%20local%20activists%20and%20these%20people%20who%20are%20actually%20doing%20the%20work%2C%20they'll%20say%20that%20the%20government%20is%20not%20doing%20a%20good%20job%20and%20that%20they%20need%20to%20move%20it%2C%20pronto%2C%20or%20the%20Ukrainians%20are%20not%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20compete.%20The%20Russians%20are%20also%20a%20lot%20better%20at%20electronic%20warfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOne%20thing%20that%20really%20surprised%20me%20with%20what%20you%20just%20said%20is%20that%20we%20have%20had%20so%20many%20high-profile%20debates%20about%20what%20next%2C%20advanced%20piece%20of%20equipment%20Ukraine%20is%20ready%20to%20get%2C%20whether%20it%20be%20F-16s%20or%20various%20missiles.%20But%20there's%20so%20many%20of%20the%20basics%20they're%20lacking%20%E2%80%94%20you're%20talking%20about%20tourniquet%20kits%20and%20armored%20vehicles.%20I%20couldn't%20imagine%20any%20concerns%20in%20Western%20capitals%20about%20those%20being%20given%20to%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20that%20a%20shock%20to%20you%3F%20What%20do%20you%20think%20explains%20the%20lack%20of%20basic%20equipment%20that%20you%20would%20think%20allies%20would've%20been%20eager%20to%20supply%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20allies%20have%20supplied%20a%20lot%20of%20this%20equipment%2C%20but%20this%20is%20more%20than%20600%20days%20of%20war.%20And%20this%20is%20a%20hot%20war%2C%20and%20they're%20burning%20through%20equipment%20very%20quickly.%20They're%20burning%20through%20shells%20very%20quickly.%20You%20can%20use%20a%20tourniquet%20once%20and%20then%20you%20got%20to%20throw%20it%20out.%20And%20ambulances%20don't%20last%20very%20long.%20Armored%20cars%20don't%20last%20very%20long.%20So%20I'm%20not%20particularly%20surprised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20talking%20to%20soldiers%20on%20the%20frontlines%2C%20they%20did%20say%2C%20overall%2C%20the%20mood%20was%20one%20of%20determination%2C%20but%20also%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20can't%20keep%20doing%20this%20without%20air%20power.%20You%20can't%20ask%20us%20to%20do%20this.%20You%20can't%20ask%20us%20to%20fight%20in%20a%20way%20you%20wouldn't%20fight%20yourself.%26quot%3B%20They're%20very%20eager%20to%20have%20air%20cover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20that%20I%20was%20surprised%20with%20is%20we%20have%20these%20intricate%20debates%20about%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20victory%3F%26quot%3B%20Does%20it%20mean%20going%20back%20to%20the%201991%20borders%3F%20Does%20it%20include%20Crimea%2C%20all%20these%20sorts%20of%20interesting%20debates.%20But%20when%20you%20go%20and%20talk%20to%20soldiers%2C%20they%20just%20want%20to%20go%20home.%20They%20want%20peace%20and%20they%20want%20to%20go%20home.%20When%20you%20talk%20to%20actual%20Ukrainians%2C%20they're%20not%20getting%20caught%20up%20in%2C%20%26quot%3BIs%20it%20Crimea%3F%20Is%20it%20the%20'91%20borders%3F%26quot%3B%20They%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20go%20home%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20want%20their%20children%20to%20be%20hit%20with%20rockets.%20It's%20a%20very%20minimal%20standard.%20They%20want%20their%20life%20to%20resume.%20They%20want%20economic%20life%20to%20resume%2C%20but%20they%20want%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22bricks%20and%20other%20debris%2C%20including%20a%20table%2C%20on%20a%20dirty%20mattress%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6539722f356802a56be4070a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20destroyed%20home%20in%20Orikhiv%2C%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EMelinda%20Haring%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWould%20it%20be%20fair%20to%20say%20that%20means%20they%20want%20an%20immediate%20ceasefire%3F%20Just%20freeze%20the%20conflict%20at%20its%20current%20boundaries%20and%20end%20the%20killing.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbsolutely%20not.%20The%20Ukrainians%20will%20continue%20to%20fight.%20Nobody%20wants%20peace%20more%20than%20Ukrainians.%20Ukrainians%20are%20tired%2C%20they're%20exhausted%2C%20and%20they%20want%20a%20normal%2C%20stable%2C%20safe%20life.%20But%20they%20are%20unwilling%20to%20give%20up%20their%20land%20and%20their%20territory.%20This%20fight%20for%20them%20is%20existential.%20If%20they%20stop%20fighting%2C%20they%20will%20lose%20their%20homelands%2C%20and%20they%20will%20lose%20their%20lives.%20So%2C%20no%2C%20they're%20not%20willing%20to%20give%20up%20their%20homeland.%20And%20Russia%20is%20not%20serious%20about%20a%20real%20negotiation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20I%20would%20also%20say%20that%20the%20Ukrainians%20feel%20like%20they%20have%20given%20too%20much.%20So%20after%20Bucha%2C%20after%20Irpin%2C%20after%20all%20of%20the%20war%20crimes%20we've%20seen%2C%20the%20Ukrainians%20have%20lost%20too%20much%20to%20concede%20any%20territory.%20And%20you%20have%20to%20remember%2C%20this%20is%20not%20Putin's%20first%20rodeo%20in%20Ukraine.%20He%20went%20in%20in%202014%2C%20and%20he%20tried%20to%20annex%20a%20big%20chunk%20of%20the%20country.%20Ukrainians%20remember%20that.%20And%20they%20know%20that%20Putin%20is%20not%20going%20to%20be%20satisfied%20with%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20let's%20give%20him%20Crimea%20in%20exchange%20for%20peace.%26quot%3B%20They%20know%20that%20he's%20going%20to%20come%20back.%20He'll%20reconstitute%20his%20forces%20and%20he'll%20be%20back%20at%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThese%20soldiers%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0you've%20just%20come%20from%20the%20frontlines%2C%20you've%20heard%20what%20they%20want.%20What%20do%20you%20say%20to%20a%20US%20senator%20who%20is%20wondering%20why%20we%20should%20keep%20supporting%20this%2C%20and%20how%20should%20that%20support%20manifest%20itself%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20say%2C%20senator%2C%20what%20happens%20in%20Ukraine%20doesn't%20stay%20in%20Ukraine.%20Yes%2C%20Ukraine%20is%205%2C000%20miles%20away%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20self-evident%20what%20US%20interests%20are%20in%20Ukraine.%20And%20I%20think%20we%20need%20to%20do%20a%20better%20job%20of%20explaining%20what%20our%20interests%20are%20there.%20But%20Putin%20is%20not%20going%20to%20be%20satisfied%20with%20Ukraine%2C%20and%20if%20he's%20able%20to%20take%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%94%20once%20he's%20able%20to%20take%20Ukraine%2C%20if%20we%20allow%20him%20to%20take%20Ukraine%2C%20I%20will%20put%20it%20that%20way%20%E2%80%94%20then%20he's%20going%20to%20go%20after%20Poland%20or%20go%20after%20a%20Baltic%20state.%20And%20the%20United%20States%20has%20treaty%20obligations%20with%20NATO%20to%20come%20to%20the%20defense%20of%20Poland%20or%20any%20of%20the%20Baltic%20states%2C%20and%20it%20will%20be%20far%20more%20expensive%20to%20fight%20Putin%20in%20a%20NATO%20country%20than%20in%20Ukraine.%20So%20let's%20stop%20him%20in%20Ukraine.%20So%20that's%20one%20reason%3A%20it's%20cheaper%20to%20do%20it%20now.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENumber%20two%20is%20the%20moral%20argument%20that%20Americans%20have%20always%20stood%20on%20the%20side%20of%20the%20underdog.%20And%20might%20doesn't%20make%20right.%20We're%20not%20going%20to%20let%20some%20bully%20rewrite%20the%20rules%20of%20the%20international%20system.%20It's%20against%20our%20nature%20as%20Americans.%20And%20I%20think%20those%20are%20the%20big%20arguments%20that%20I%20would%20use%20for%20a%20congressman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20I%20think%20the%20third%20one%20is%20probably%20even%20the%20most%20important%2C%20that%20what%20happens%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20having%20an%20effect%20around%20the%20world.%20So%20if%20we%20allow%20Putin%20to%20get%20away%20with%20it%2C%20then%20he's%20going%20to%20go%20after%20Taiwan%2C%20and%20we're%20going%20to%20see%20more%20of%20this%20kind%20of%20behavior%20everywhere%2C%20and%20that's%20not%20a%20world%20that%20I%20want%20to%20live%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWas%20there%20anything%20else%20from%20your%20trip%20that%20was%20surprising%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20attitude%20is%20just%20so%20different.%20I%20went%20and%20met%20with%20the%20authorities%20in%20Zaporizhzhia%2C%20and%20we%20had%20a%20nice%20chat%2C%20and%20I%20was%20asking%20them%20what%20they're%20worried%20about.%20They're%20not%20worried%20about%20the%20Russians%20hitting%20the%20nuclear%20power%20plant.%20The%20Russians%20do%20not%20have%20enough%20precise%20rockets%20to%20hit%20the%20power%20plant%2C%20and%20they%20have%20enough%20air%20defense%20systems%20to%20protect%20the%20power%20plant.%20So%20CNN%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20big%20media%20in%20the%20US%20have%20done%20a%20lot%20of%20reporting%20on%20the%20power%20plant%2C%20of%20course.%20And%20the%20locals%20are%20not%20very%20worried%20about%20it.%20They%20said%2C%20worst-case%20scenario%20is%20that%20there%20will%20be%20two%20to%20three%20weeks%20of%20blackouts.%20Ukraine%20is%20expecting%20the%20Russians%20to%20hit%20the%20grid%20again%20and%20to%20try%20to%20bring%20down%20critical%20infrastructure.%20And%20they're%20not%20terribly%20worried%20about%20it.%20They're%20prepared%20for%20it.%20The%20Russians%20did%20it%20last%20year%2C%20so%20there's%20no%20element%20of%20surprise%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20I%20asked%20my%20favorite%20American%20question%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20policies%20and%20programs%20are%20you%20putting%20in%20place%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20everyone%20gets%20through%20the%20winter%20and%20that%20people's%20spirits%20are%20restored%3F%26quot%3B%20And%20they%20looked%20at%20me%20like%20I%20was%20an%20alien%2C%20and%20they%20said%2C%20we%20don't%20need%20that%20stuff.%20And%20I%20said%2C%20pardon%20me%3F%20They%20said%2C%20we%20don't%20need%20your%20programs.%20We%20need%20a%20hundred%20bomb%20shelters%20so%20we%20can%20reopen%20our%20schools.