sinessinsider.com%2Fcar-buyer-interest-hybrids-as-electric-vehicle-adoption-slowing-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698486721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653bd07296f7540cd067a67c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcar-buyer-interest-hybrids-as-electric-vehicle-adoption-slowing-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Car%20shoppers%20are%20desperate%20for%20more%20hybrid%20options%20as%20demand%20for%20pure%20electrics%20cools.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nnaughton%40insider.com%20(Nora%20Naughton%2CAlexa%20St.%20John)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcar-buyer-interest-hybrids-as-electric-vehicle-adoption-slowing-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hamas%20militants%20were%20high%20on%20'poor%20man's%20cocaine'%20during%20the%20October%207%20terrorist%20attacks%2C%20report%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226932%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Lebanese%20security%20official%20with%20a%20handful%20of%20confiscated%20Captagon%20pills%20in%20his%20palm%20at%20the%20judicial%20police%20headquarters%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Zahle%20in%20Lebanon's%20central%20Bekaa%20valley%20on%20July%2021%2C%202022%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6538f1e9356802a56be32388%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225199%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Lebanese%20security%20official%20with%20a%20handful%20of%20confiscated%20Captagon%20pills%20in%20his%20palm%20at%20the%20judicial%20police%20headquarters%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Zahl%C3%A9%20in%20Lebanon's%20central%20Bekaa%20valley%20on%20July%2021%2C%202022%3Cp%3EJOSEPH%20EID%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EHamas%20militants%20were%20high%20on%20Captagon%20pills%20during%20the%20October%207%20terrorist%20attacks%2C%20reports%20say.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ECaptagon%20is%20a%20brand%20name%20of%20the%20synthetic%20stimulant%20fenethylline%20hydrochloride.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EMilitant%20groups%20use%20the%20drug%20to%20increase%20%26quot%3Baggressiveness%2C%20alertness%2C%20and%20fearlessness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECaptagon%20pills%20fueled%20Hamas%20militants%20during%20the%20October%207%20terrorist%20attacks%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mako.co.il%2Fnews-military%2F6361323ddea5a810%2FArticle-8a78e9c58574b81027.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIsrael's%20Channel%2012%20News%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drug%2C%20which%20is%20also%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bpoor%20man's%20cocaine%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20highly%20addictive%2C%20synthetic%20stimulant%20that%20is%20widely%20consumed%20across%20the%20Middle%20East.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Hebrew-language%20news%20channel%20reported%20that%20pills%20of%20the%20drug%20had%20been%20found%20on%20the%20bodies%20of%20Hamas%20prisoners%20and%20fighters%20killed%20in%20the%20conflict%2C%20suggesting%20that%20they%20had%20taken%20the%20drug%20before%20carrying%20out%20their%20%26quot%3Binhumane%20murders.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20IDF%20told%20Insider%20by%20email%20that%20it%20did%20%26quot%3Bnot%20have%20information%20or%20a%20comment%20on%20this%20subject.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIsraeli%20security%20guards%20in%20the%20southern%20West%20Bank%20stopped%20thousands%20of%20Captagon%20pills%20hidden%20in%20a%20shipment%20of%20refrigerators%20from%20being%20smuggled%20into%20Gaza%20in%20January%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesofisrael.com%2Fsecurity-guards-foil-attempt-to-smuggle-islamic-state-drug-from-west-bank-to-gaza%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Times%20of%20Israel%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%201%2C400%20people%20were%20killed%20in%20Israel%20during%20the%20attacks%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20while%20over%20200%20people%20were%20also%20taken%20hostage%20by%20Hamas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFenethylline%20hydrochloride%20and%20the%20Middle%20East%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECaptagon%20is%20the%20brand%20name%20of%20the%20drug%20fenethylline%20hydrochloride.%20The%20substance%20was%20created%20in%20the%201960s%20in%20West%20Germany%20to%20help%20treat%20conditions%20such%20as%20attention%20deficit%20disorder%2C%20depression%2C%20and%20narcolepsy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20highly%20addictive%20nature%20led%20to%20it%20being%20banned%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20but%20a%20clandestine%20trade%20of%20counterfeit%20versions%20of%20the%20pills%20began%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20Its%20popularity%20particularly%20blossomed%20in%20Gulf%20states%20like%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Qatar%2C%20and%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20Israeli%20military%20action%20against%20the%20militant%20group%20Hezbollah%20in%20Lebanon%20in%202006%2C%20production%20of%20Captagon%20increased%20in%20Lebanon%20as%20the%20group%20sought%20to%20build%20up%20its%20depleted%20finances%2C%20and%20production%20became%20rife%20along%20the%20Syrian%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drug%2C%20a%20mixture%20of%20amphetamine%20and%20theophylline%2C%20often%20cut%20with%20other%20substances%20such%20as%20caffeine%20and%20paracetamol%2C%20became%20particularly%20popular%20with%20fighters%20in%20the%20Syrian%20civil%20war%20and%20with%20Islamic%20State%20(ISIS)%2C%20as%20they%20sought%20to%20stave%20off%20sleep%20and%20remain%20focused.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.acs.org%2Fmolecule-of-the-week%2Farchive%2Ff%2Ffenethylline-hydrochloride.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Chemical%20Society%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20militant%20groups%20use%20the%20drug%20to%20increase%20what%20they%20deem%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bdesirable%20characteristics%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20fighters%2C%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Baggressiveness%2C%20alertness%2C%20and%20fearlessness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drug%20has%20since%20become%20a%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20revenue%20stream%26quot%3B%20for%20Syrian%20President%20Bashar%20Assad's%20regime%2C%20helping%20it%20%26quot%3Bstay%20afloat%20as%20sanctions%20and%20other%20economic%20measures%20are%20squeezing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Natalie%20Ecanow%2C%20a%20research%20analyst%20at%20the%20think%20tank%20The%20Foundation%20for%20Defense%20of%20Democracies%20(FDD)%2C%20which%20focuses%20on%20Lebanon%2C%20Jordan%2C%20and%20the%20Levant%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Fnews%2Ftackling-the-illicit-drug-trade-fuelling-assads-war-machine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUK%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20around%2080%25%20of%20the%20global%20supply%20of%20the%20drug%20is%20produced%20in%20the%20country%2C%20and%20Assad%20%26quot%3Bhas%20been%20able%20to%20leverage%20the%20drug%20trade%26quot%3B%20to%20gain%20concessions%20from%20other%20Arab%20leaders%2C%C2%A0%20Ecanow%20added%20%E2%80%94%20which%20led%20to%20his%20eventual%20welcome%20back%20into%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F5%2F19%2Fassad-gets-warm-welcome-as-syria-welcomed-back-into-arab-league%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAfter%2520more%2520than%2520a%2520decade%2Cback%2520into%2520the%2520Arab%2520League.%5C%22%3EArab%20League%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Syrian%20regime's%20trafficking%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars'%20worth%20of%20captagon%20has%20helped%20to%20spread%20violence%20across%20the%20region%3B%20Hamas%20terrorists'%20reported%20use%20of%20the%20drug%20only%20adds%20to%20the%20carnage%2C%26quot%3B%20David%20Adesnik%2C%20Senior%20Fellow%20and%20Director%20of%20Research%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fdd.org%2Fanalysis%2F2023%2F10%2F21%2Fhamas-killers-in-israel-reportedly-fueled-by-captagon%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFDD%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222637%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22assad%20syria%20bashar%20al-assad%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653a8c5a356802a56be4c9d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221978%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESyrian%20President%20Bashar%20Assad.%3Cp%3ESANA%20via%20AP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20key%20link%20to%20Assad's%20regime%20came%20in%202018%2C%20when%20the%20cargo%20ship%20Noka%2C%20sailing%20from%20the%20Syrian%20port%20of%20Latakia%20to%20eastern%20Libya%2C%20was%20raided%20as%20it%20passed%20the%20Greek%20island%20of%20Crete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20board%2C%20authorities%20discovered%20more%20than%20%24100%20million%20worth%20of%20cannabis%20and%20Captagon%20pills%20that%20had%20been%20hidden%20among%20sawdust%2C%20coffee%2C%20and%20spices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20later%2C%20Italian%20police%20seized%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20hauls%20of%20Captagon%20after%20they%20found%2014%20tonnes%20of%20the%20drug%2C%20worth%20around%201%20billion%20euros%2C%20just%20over%20%241%20billion%2C%20at%20the%20port%20of%20Salerno%2C%20near%20Naples%20in%20southern%20Italy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.occrp.org%2Fen%2Finvestigations%2Fgreek-captagon-bust-leads-to-a-criminal-gang-and-the-port-at-the-heart-of-syrias-booming-new-drug-trade%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOrganized%20Crime%20and%20Corruption%20Reporting%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%20(OCCRP)%2C%20a%20combination%20of%20ship%20tracking%20data%2C%20court%20documents%2C%20company%20data%2C%20and%20information%20from%20authorities%20linked%20many%20of%20these%20Captagon%20hauls%20back%20to%20the%20Mediterranean%20port%20of%20Latakia%2C%20Syria's%20main%20port.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20OCCRP%20describes%20Latakia%20as%20%26quot%3Ban%20impenetrable%20Assad%20fiefdom%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20controlled%20by%20Assad's%20brother%2C%20Maher%20Al-Assad%2C%20and%20his%20notorious%20Fourth%20Division%20army.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20data%20on%20seizures%20in%20the%20region%20valued%20the%20Captagon%20trade%20at%20%245.7%20billion%2C%20per%20the%20FDD.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhamas-militants-high-poor-mans-cocaine-oct-7-attacks-report-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698486607000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653cd845356802a56be6bd87%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhamas-militants-high-poor-mans-cocaine-oct-7-attacks-report-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20the%20American%20Chemical%20Society%2C%20militant%20groups%20use%20the%20Captagon%20to%20increase%20%26quot%3Baggressiveness%2C%20alertness%2C%20and%20fearlessness.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nrennolds%40insider.com%20(Nathan%20Rennolds)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhamas-militants-high-poor-mans-cocaine-oct-7-attacks-report-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Full%20Text%3A%20%E2%80%98Israel%20Does%20Not%20Want%20Palestine%20as%20Partner%20in%20Peace%2C%20Wants%20To%20Maintain%20Control%20Over%20It'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F28151151%2Fmaxresdefault.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOn%20October%2025%2C%20Karan%20Thapar%20spoke%20to%20Avi%20Shlaim%2C%20emeritus%20professor%20of%20international%20relations%2C%20St.%20Antony%E2%80%99s%20College%2C%20Oxford.%20Shlaim%2C%20the%20acclaimed%20author%20of%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%3A%20Reappraisals%2C%20Revisions%20Refutations%20and%20The%20Iron%20Wall%3A%20Israel%20and%20the%20Arab%20World%2C%20spoke%20about%20the%20history%20of%20the%20conflict%20and%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20October%207%20attack%20by%20Hamas.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20the%20interview%2C%20they%20discuss%20various%20issues%20and%20some%20statements%20by%20Avi%20Shlaim%20are%20highlighted%20below.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Land%20grabbing%20and%20peacemaking%20don%E2%80%99t%20go%20together%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20one%20or%20the%20other%2C%20and%20by%20constantly%20expanding%20settlements%2C%20Israel%20showed%20that%20it%20prefers%20land%20to%20peace.%E2%80%99%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Israel%20by%20its%20actions%20has%20shown%20that%20it%20is%20not%20interested%20in%20having%20a%20Palestinian%20partner%20for%20peace%20because%20it%20wants%20to%20maintain%20its%20control%20over%20the%20territory.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Israel%20refuses%20to%20accept%20Hamas%20as%20a%20negotiating%20partner.%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20position%20is%20that%20Hamas%20is%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20%E2%80%93%20pure%20and%20simple.%20It%20will%20never%20negotiate%20with%20it.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Benjamin%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20policy%20has%20been%20to%20let%20Hamas%20rule%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20but%20to%20contain%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20and%20this%20policy%20collapsed%2C%20because%20Gaza%20could%20not%20be%20contained.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98What%20Israel%20refuses%20to%20do%20is%20to%20accept%20that%20Hamas%20represents%20a%20serious%20body%20of%20Palestinians%2C%20and%20that%20you%20cannot%20reach%20any%20peace%20agreement%20with%20the%20Palestinians%20that%20excludes%20Hamas.%20So%2C%20the%20sensible%20thing%20for%20Israel%20to%20do%20and%20the%20other%20European%20powers%20to%20do%20is%20to%20recognise%20Hamas%20and%20to%20negotiate%20with%20Hamas%20for%20a%20political%20settlement%20of%20the%20conflict.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98This%20is%20a%20political%20conflict%20between%20the%20two%20sides%2C%20but%20Israel%20only%20uses%20brute%20military%20force%20to%20suppress%20the%20Palestinians%20on%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20in%20Gaza%2C%20and%20nothing%20but%20brute%20military%20force.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98What%20we%20are%20witnessing%20today%2C%20day%20after%20day%2C%20in%20Gaza%20is%20Israel%20moving%20towards%20ethnic%20cleansing%20of%20the%20population%20and%20genocide.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98The%20West%20also%20bears%20a%20part%20of%20the%20responsibility%20for%20the%20present%20and%20past%2C%20because%20of%20its%20massive%20support%20for%20Israel%2C%20its%20supply%20of%20arms%20to%20Israel%2C%20and%20its%20diplomatic%20protection%20of%20Israel.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98My%20duty%20as%20a%20public%20intellectual%2C%20and%20as%20a%20student%20of%20this%20conflict%2C%20is%20to%20give%20the%20public%E2%80%A6%20an%20account%20of%20the%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%20which%20is%20as%20truthful%20as%20possible%2C%20as%20honest%20as%20possible%2C%20and%20as%20fair-minded%20as%20possible.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBelow%20is%20a%20transcript%20of%20the%20full%20interview%2C%20edited%20lightly%20for%20style%2C%20clarity%20and%20syntax.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20%3Cstrong%3EHello%20and%20welcome%20to%20a%20special%20interview%20for%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E.%20As%20we%20approach%20the%20end%20of%20three%20weeks%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20conflict%2C%20we%20ask%2C%20do%20we%20really%20know%20and%20understand%20the%20history%20of%20the%20relationship%20and%20struggle%20between%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%3F%20There%20are%20many%20who%20believe%20that%20until%20history%20is%20properly%20understood%2C%20you%20cannot%20really%20understand%20why%20%5Bthe%20incident%20on%5D%20October%207%20happened.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJoining%20me%20now%20from%20Oxford%20is%20someone%20who%20is%20going%20to%20explain%20to%20us%20the%20history%20as%20he%20sees%20it.%20Professor%20Avi%20Shlaim%20is%20an%20Emeritus%20Professor%20of%20International%20Relations%20at%20Oxford%20University%20and%20the%20author%20of%20seminal%20books%20on%20the%20subject%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ci%3EIsrael%20and%20Palestine%3A%20Reappraisals%2C%20Revisions%20Refutations%3C%2Fi%3E%20and%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Iron%20Wall%3A%20Israel%20and%20the%20Arab%20World.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%2C%20in%20your%20books%20and%20essays%2C%20you%20trace%20the%20origin%20of%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20conflict%20to%20the%2019th%20century%20Zionist%20movement%2C%20which%20sought%20to%20create%20an%20independent%20Jewish%20state%20in%20Palestine%2C%20in%20which%20Jews%20would%20constitute%20the%20majority.%20But%20you%20say%20the%20principal%20problem%20with%20this%20project%20was%20that%20Palestine%20was%20already%20home%20to%20an%20Arab%20population%20that%20had%20lived%20there%20for%20centuries.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20were%2C%20therefore%2C%20two%20peoples%20and%20one%20land%2C%20hence%20the%20conflict.%20Are%20you%20also%20suggesting%2C%20Professor%20Shlaim%2C%20that%20the%20Zionist%20claim%20to%20Palestine%20was%20not%20justified%20or%20was%20at%20least%20based%20on%20weak%20grounds%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20Zionist%20claim%20to%20Palestine%20was%20based%20on%20exceptionally%20weak%20grounds%20and%20a%20misrepresentation%20of%20the%20reality%20in%20Palestine%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%2019th%20century.%20There%20was%20a%20very%20clever%20Zionist%20slogan%3A%20a%20country%20without%20a%20people%20for%20a%20people%20without%20a%20country.%20The%20slogan%20implied%20that%20the%20Jews%20were%20people%20without%20a%20country%2C%20which%20they%20were%2C%20but%20it%20also%20implied%20that%20Palestine%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20people%2C%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20inhabited%20but%20this%20was%20not%20true.%20There%20had%20been%20a%20well-constituted%20Arab%20society%20in%20Palestine%20for%20centuries.%20And%20the%20Zionist%20claim%20to%20Palestine%20was%20also%20not%20very%20convincing%20because%20Zionism%20was%20a%20secular%20movement%2C%20but%20it%20also%20invoked%20divine%20promise%20to%20the%20Jews%20of%20the%20promised%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20zionists%20were%20secular%2C%20they%20did%20not%20believe%20in%20God%20and%20yet%20they%20turned%20God%20into%20a%20land%20agent%20who%20promised%20them%20this%20particular%20plot%20of%20land.%20The%20weakness%20of%20the%20Zionist%20claim%20to%20Palestine%20is%20illustrated%20by%20the%20following%20episode.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20visionary%20of%20the%20Jewish%20state%20was%20Theodore%20Herzl%2C%20a%20Viennese%20Jew%2C%20who%20wrote%20a%20pamphlet%20outlining%20his%20idea%20for%20a%20Jewish%20state%20in%20Palestine%2C%20and%20the%20rabbis%20of%20Vienna%20got%20together%2C%20collected%20some%20money%2C%20and%20sent%20two%20of%20their%20members%20to%20Palestine%20to%20check%20out%20Herzl%E2%80%99s%20idea%20and%20the%20two%20rabbis%20sent%20a%20telegram%20which%20became%20famous.%20It%20said%20that%20the%20bride%20is%20beautiful%20but%20she%20is%20already%20married%20to%20another%20man.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20Palestine%20is%20beautiful%20but%20there%20were%20already%20other%20people%20living%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3A%20As%20a%20historian%2C%20how%20do%20you%20evaluate%20a%20more%20emotional%20claim%20that%20the%20Jews%20make%20to%20the%20land%20of%20Palestine%20that%20it%20is%20their%20biblical%20heritage%3F%20That%20it%20is%20the%20land%20of%20Canaan.%20This%20is%20where%20Judaism%20started.%20Therefore%2C%20this%20is%20our%20home.%20How%20do%20you%20evaluate%20that%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20This%20claim%20is%20completely%20invalid%20in%20the%20modern%20era.%20In%20the%20modern%20era%2C%20there%20is%20international%20law%2C%20there%20are%20international%20organisations%2C%20there%20are%20international%20borders%2C%20and%20a%20claim%20that%20goes%20back%20to%20two%20millennia%20ago%20is%20completely%20untenable%20in%20the%20modern%20age.%20Because%20any%20other%20people%20could%20resurrect%20claims%20that%20go%20back%20millennia%20ago%2C%20and%20if%20every%20person%20was%20able%20to%20assert%20historic%20rights%20to%20a%20land%2C%20then%20that%20is%20a%20recipe%20for%20never-ending%20conflict%20all%20over%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHaving%20said%20that%2C%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20deny%20the%20very%20strong%20emotional%20and%20historic%20association%20between%20the%20Jewish%20people%20and%20Zion.%20Zion%20is%20one%20of%20the%20many%20names%20for%20Jerusalem%2C%20so%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20deny%20the%20association%20and%20of%20course%2C%20Jerusalem%20is%20particularly%20of%20huge%20symbolic%20and%20religious%20importance%20to%20the%20Jewish%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJews%20for%20centuries%20have%20been%20praying%2C%20Jews%20everywhere%20have%20been%20praying%20in%20Jerusalem.%20That%20was%20the%20ultimate%20aspiration%20to%20return%20to%20Zion%2C%20but%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20make%20it%20a%20politically%20or%20legally%20valid%20claim%20to%20the%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%20Israel%20came%20into%20being%2C%20Professor%20Shlaim%2C%20in%201948%20and%20that%20very%20quickly%20led%20to%20the%20expulsion%20of%20some%20750%2C000%20Palestinians%20from%20their%20lands%2C%20which%20they%20called%20the%20%3Cem%3Enakba%3C%2Fem%3E.%20In%20an%20article%20that%20you%20wrote%20for%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fi%3E%20in%202009%2C%20you%20said%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20you%20here%2C%20%E2%80%9CEstablishing%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20in%20May%201948%20involved%20a%20monumental%20injustice%20to%20the%20Palestinians.%E2%80%9D%20Was%20that%20the%20start%20of%20the%20modern-day%20Israel-Palestine%20conflict%20as%20well%20as%20the%20deep-seated%20sense%20of%20hurt%20and%20grievance%20that%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20feel%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%5BIn%5D%201948%2C%20the%20establishment%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20and%20the%20first%20Arab-Israeli%20War%20was%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20the%20modern%20history%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20but%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20choose%20that%20year%20to%20mark%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20had%20to%20choose%20an%20arbitrary%20date%20for%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20conflict%2C%20I%20would%20opt%20for%201917.%20That%20is%20the%20year%20in%20which%20Britain%20issued%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fevent%2FBalfour-Declaration%5C%22%3EBalfour%20Declaration%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20support%20of%20a%20national%20home%20for%20the%20Jewish%20people%20in%20Palestine.%20So%2C%20this%20is%20a%20really%20significant%20document%20in%20which%20Britain%20allocated%20to%20the%20Jews%20political%20right%2C%20the%20right%20to%20national%20self-determination%2C%20and%20denied%20it%20to%20the%20Arabs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201917%2C%20the%20Jews%20were%20only%2010%25%20of%20the%20population%2C%20the%20Arabs%20were%2090%25.%20The%20Jews%20owned%20only%202%25%20of%20the%20land%2C%20and%20yet%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20enabled%20the%20Zionist%20movement%20to%20embark%20on%20the%20systematic%20takeover%20of%20Palestine%20which%20continues%20to%20this%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20I%20would%20say%20that%20the%20British%20mandate%20in%20Palestine%20from%201922%20to%201948%20is%20what%20enabled%20the%20Zionist%20movement%20to%20establish%20itself%2C%20and%20%5Bit%20also%20enabled%20them%5D%20to%20eventually%2C%20in%201948%2C%20proclaim%20and%20achieve%20independence.%20Now%2C%20I%20have%20never%20questioned%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20within%20its%20original%20borders.%20These%20are%20the%20borders%20that%20were%20agreed%20upon%20between%20Israel%20and%20its%20neighbours%20in%201949%20after%20the%20guns%20fell%20silent.%20These%20are%20the%20only%20internationally%20recognised%20borders%20that%20Israel%20has%20ever%20had%20and%20the%20ones%20that%20I%20still%20regard%20as%20legitimate%2C%20but%20there%20is%20no%20denying%20that%20the%20establishment%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20involved%20a%20monumental%20injustice%20to%20the%20Palestinians.%20This%20is%20what%20the%20Palestinians%20call%20the%20%3Cem%3Enakba%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20catastrophe.%20Three-fourths%20of%20a%20million%20Palestinians%2C%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20Arab%20population%20became%20refugees%2C%20and%20the%20name%20Palestine%20was%20wiped%20off%20the%20map.%20This%20is%20the%20%3Cem%3ENakba%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20this%20is%20the%20catastrophe.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20%3Cstrong%3EI%E2%80%99ll%20just%20point%20out%20for%20the%20audience%2C%20professor%20Shlaim%2C%20that%20although%20you%20accept%20that%201948%20was%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20history%2C%20the%20actual%20origin%20of%20the%20problem%20goes%20back%20to%20the%20Balfour%20Declaration%20of%201917%2C%20which%20is%20why%20many%20Palestinians%20believe%20that%20the%20original%20responsibility%20for%20the%20creation%20of%20Israel%2C%20and%20for%20the%20problems%20between%20Israel%20and%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20is%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20a%20British%20responsibility%20and%20you%20explained%20that%20very%20well.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20years%20that%20followed%201948%2C%20the%20Arab%20nations%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%20rejected%20Israel.%20They%20fought%20wars%20with%20Israel%2C%20but%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fevent%2FSix-Day-War%5C%22%3ESix-Day%20War%20of%201967%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20Israel%20captured%20the%20Sinai%20Peninsula%2C%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20and%20the%20Golan%20Heights%2C%20it%20agreed%20to%20trade%20land%20for%20peace.%20That%20could%20have%20led%20to%20a%20solution%2C%20but%20Israel%20reneged%20on%20its%20commitments%20and%20instead%20started%20to%20build%20settlements%20in%20the%20occupied%20territories.%20Of%20this%2C%20you%20write%2C%20%E2%80%9Crefusal%20to%20relinquish%20the%20fruits%20of%20its%20military%20victory%20turned%20little%20Israel%20into%20a%20colonial%20power%20ruling%20over%20a%20recalcitrant%20Arab%20population.%E2%80%9D%20Why%20did%20Israel%20do%20this%3F%20Why%20did%20it%20deliberately%20throw%20away%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20solution%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20June%201967%20war%20was%20another%20historic%20turning%20point%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20For%20the%20first%20time%2C%20Israel%20had%20something%20concrete%20that%20it%20could%20offer%20to%20the%20Arabs%20in%20return%20for%20peace%2C%20because%20in%20the%20course%20of%20the%20war%2C%20Israel%20travelled%20%5Bexpanded%5D%20its%20territory.%20It%20captured%20the%20Golan%20Heights%20from%20Syria%2C%20the%20West%20Bank%20from%20Jordan%2C%20and%20the%20Sinai%20Peninsula%20from%20Egypt.%20And%20the%20King%20Hussein%20of%20Jordan%2C%20immediately%20after%20the%20end%20of%20hostilities%2C%20offered%20Israel%20total%20peace%20for%20total%20withdrawal.%20But%20Israel%20did%20not%20accept%20this%20offer%2C%20and%20Israel%20started%20building%20settlements%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20and%20in%20Gaza%2C%20and%20in%20the%20Golan%20Heights.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhy%20did%20Israel%20not%20agree%20to%20trade%20land%20for%20peace%2C%20now%20that%20it%20had%20the%20opportunity%3F%20The%20answer%20to%20that%20is%2C%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20victory%2C%20there%20was%20a%20convergence%20of%20secular%20nationalism%20with%20religious%20nationalism%2C%20and%20both%20secular%20Israelis%20and%20religious%20Israelis%20felt%20that%20this%20was%20an%20opportunity%20to%20realise%20the%20land%20of%20Israel.%20The%20land%20of%20Israel%20was%20a%20concept%2C%20and%20now%20they%20wanted%20to%20turn%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20into%20the%20land%20of%20Israel%2C%20by%20incorporating%20the%20West%20Bank%20into%20Greater%20Israel.%20The%20West%20Bank%2C%20or%20as%20right-wing%20Israelis%20prefer%20to%20call%20it%2C%20Judea%20and%20Samaria%2C%20prefer%20the%20biblical%20rights.%20So%2C%20it%20was%20the%20surge%20of%20powerful%20nationalism%20in%20Israel%20that%20militated%20against%20a%20compromise%2C%20and%20the%20settlements%20are%20one%20of%20the%20factors%20that%20have%20not%20only%20been%20illegal%2C%20but%20also%20remain%20the%20main%20obstacle%20to%20peace%20between%20Israel%20and%20the%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3EWas%20this%20a%20missed%20opportunity%3F%20%5BWas%20it%5D%20A%20moment%20when%20Israel%20could%20actually%20have%20established%20a%20peaceful%20relationship%20with%20its%20Arab%20neighbours%3F%20Did%20it%20miss%20the%20opportunity%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EMost%20definitely%2C%20it%20was%20a%20missed%20opportunity%20on%20the%20part%20of%20Israel.%20The%20United%20Nations%20offered%20a%20formula%20for%20a%20settlement.%20UN%20Resolution%20242%20offered%20Israel%20peace%20and%20security%20in%20return%20for%20giving%20up%20the%20territories%20it%20had%20conquered%20in%20the%20course%20of%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20formula%20that%20%5Bhad%5D%20worked.%20When%20Israel%20%5Bhad%5D%20applied%20the%20formula%20242%2C%20in%201979%2C%20it%20got%20a%20peace%20agreement%20with%20Egypt.%20Israel%20had%20to%20give%20back%20the%20whole%20of%20the%20Sinai%20Peninsula%2C%20but%20in%20return%20it%20got%20peace.%20Israel%20could%20have%20had%20peace%20with%20Syria%20if%20it%20had%20agreed%20to%20return%20the%20whole%20of%20the%20Golan%20Heights%20to%20Syrian%20sovereignty.%20And%20as%20I%20just%20said%2C%20King%20Hussein%20of%20Jordan%20also%20offered%20Israel%20land%20for%20peace%2C%20but%20Israel%20missed%20the%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%201967%2C%20Israel%20had%20a%20basic%20choice%20to%20make%2C%20land%20or%20peace%20with%20its%20neighbours%2C%20and%20in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20Israel%20has%20opted%20for%20land%2C%20in%20preference%20to%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26153147%2F1200px-Flickr_-_Government_Press_Office_GPO_-_Arab_People_fleeing.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26153147%2F1200px-Flickr_-_Government_Press_Office_GPO_-_Arab_People_fleeing.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26153147%2F1200px-Flickr_-_Government_Press_Office_GPO_-_Arab_People_fleeing-300x202.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26153147%2F1200px-Flickr_-_Government_Press_Office_GPO_-_Arab_People_fleeing-1024x689.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681847%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22807%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPalestinians%20fleeing%20their%20homes%20after%20the%20establishment%20of%20Israel%20in%201948.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FDavid%20Eldan%2FCC%20BY-SA%203.0%20DEED%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20next%20opportunity%20for%20a%20solution%2C%20Professor%20Shlaim%2C%20came%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhistory.state.gov%2Fmilestones%2F1993-2000%2Foslo%5C%22%3E1993%20Oslo%20Accords%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20write%2C%20%E2%80%9COslo%20achieved%20three%20things%2C%20the%20PLO%20recognised%20Israel%2C%20Israel%20recognised%20the%20PLO%20as%20the%20representative%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people%2C%20and%20the%20two%20sides%20agreed%20to%20resolve%20their%20outstanding%20differences%20by%20peaceful%20means.%E2%80%9D%20This%20led%20the%20Palestinians%20to%20believe%20that%20they%20could%20gain%20an%20independent%20state%20with%20a%20capital%20in%20Jerusalem%2C%20but%20this%20never%20happened.%20What%20went%20wrong%3F%20And%20who%2C%20in%20your%20opinion%2C%20is%20more%20to%20blame%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20Oslo%20Accord%20which%20happened%2030%20years%20ago%20last%20month%20was%20a%20very%20modest%20step%20in%20the%20right%20direction%2C%20and%20at%20the%20time%2C%20when%20the%20Oslo%20Accord%20was%20signed%2C%20I%20was%20euphoric.%20I%20thought%20that%20this%20is%20the%20real%20deal%2C%20%5Bthat%5D%20this%20is%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20solution%2C%20because%20I%20believed%20that%20it%20would%20start%20a%20process%20of%20gradual%20controlled%20Israeli%20withdrawal%20from%20the%20occupied%20territories%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20which%20there%20would%20be%20a%20Palestinian%20state%2C%20but%20I%20was%20wrong.%20Now%2C%20the%20Oslo%20Peace%20process%20broke%20down.%20Why%20did%20it%20break%20down%3F%20There%20are%20two%20different%20explanations%3A%20there%20is%20the%20official%20Israeli%20explanation%2C%20which%20says%20Oslo%20broke%20down%20because%20the%20Palestinians%20returned%20to%20violence%2C%20and%20it%20is%20terrorism%20that%20destroyed%20the%20Accord.%20And%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20never%20accepted%20the%20Oslo%20Accord%2C%20and%20so%20he%20rejected%20it%20from%20the%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMy%20explanation%20is%20that%20it%20is%20Israel%20%E2%80%93%20which%20after%20the%20murder%20of%20Yitzhak%20Rabin%2C%20and%20the%20return%20to%20power%20of%20the%20Likud%20right-wing%20party%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%20in%201996%20%E2%80%93%20that%20reneged%20on%20its%20side%20of%20the%20deal.%20And%20if%20you%20press%20me%20to%20say%20in%20one%20word%2C%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Oslo%20Peace%20process%2C%20that%20word%20is%20%E2%80%98settlements%E2%80%99.%20Jewish%20settlements%20on%20the%20West%20Bank%20represent%20land%20grabbing%2C%20stealing%20land%20that%20belongs%20to%20the%20Palestinians.%20Land%20grabbing%20and%20peacemaking%20don%E2%80%99t%20go%20together%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20one%20or%20the%20other%2C%20and%20by%20constantly%20expanding%20settlements%2C%20Israel%20showed%20that%20it%20prefers%20land%20to%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisrael-palestine-jewish-voice-for-peace-apartheid%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Not%20in%20Our%20Name%E2%80%99%3A%20The%20Jews%20Who%20Refuse%20to%20Be%20Bystanders%20to%20Historic%20Injustice%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%20me%20quote%20from%20your%20writings.%20You%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20change%20of%20government%20from%20Labor%20to%20Likud%20had%20profound%20implications%20for%20the%20peace%20process%20and%20the%20reason%20is%2C%20Likud%20explicitly%20rejected%20the%20idea%20of%20an%20independent%20Palestinian%20state%20alongside%20Israel.%E2%80%9D%20And%20the%20Likud%20leader%20was%20none%20other%20than%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu.%20So%2C%20does%20he%20bear%20a%20certain%20measure%20of%20personal%20responsibility%20because%20of%20the%20position%20he%20took%2C%20for%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%20collapsed%20and%20were%20not%20fulfilled%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3ENetanyahu%20bears%20a%20very%20very%20large%20share%20of%20the%20responsibility%20for%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%20because%20when%20he%20was%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%2C%20he%20led%20a%20campaign%20of%20incitement%20against%20the%20Rabin%20government%2C%20the%20democratically%20elected%20government%2C%20and%20this%20incitement%20ended%20with%20the%20assassination%20of%20Yitzhak%20Rabin.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20he%20was%20never%20committed%20to%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%2C%20and%20once%20he%20was%20elected%20in%201996%2C%20and%20he%20was%20elected%20by%20a%20margin%20of%20less%20than%201%25%2C%20and%20yet%20he%20immediately%20proceeded%20to%20undermine%20and%20subvert%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%20and%20reestablish%20Israeli%20control%20over%20the%20whole%20of%20the%20West%20Bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELabour%20built%20settlements%20only%20in%20areas%20that%20they%20thought%20were%20strategically%20important.%20The%20Likud%20under%20Netanyahu%20has%20built%20settlements%20across%20the%20length%20and%20breadth%20of%20the%20West%20Bank%20in%20order%20to%20make%20territorial%20compromise%20impossible.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20fact%2C%20you%20make%20this%20point%20very%20strongly%20in%20your%20work.%20Since%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%2C%20Israeli%20settlements%20on%20the%20West%20Bank%20have%20proliferated%20to%20the%20point%20that%20there%20are%20now%20some%20750%2C000%20settlers%2C%20I%20believe%2C%20in%20the%20West%20Bank.%20In%20Gaza%2C%20Israel%20occupied%20the%20Strip%2C%20then%20after%20vacating%20it%2C%20blockaded%20it%20and%20surrounded%20it%20virtually%20from%20all%20sides%2C%20restricting%20imports%20and%20exports.%20And%20even%20when%20it%20took%20over%20the%20whole%20of%20Jerusalem%20as%20its%20capital%2C%20it%20once%20again%20gave%20a%20signal%20that%20there%20was%20no%20question%20of%20Jerusalem%20being%20shared.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDoes%20this%20mean%20that%20in%20the%20last%2010-15%20years%2C%20maybe%20a%20bit%20longer%2C%20Israel%20has%20effectively%20buried%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%20deep%20underground%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EIt%20does%20mean%20that%20Israel%20has%20completely%20turned%20its%20back%20on%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%2C%20and%20if%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20intention%2C%20if%20its%20purpose%20was%20to%20proceed%20to%20peace%20with%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20then%20it%20would%20support%20a%20strong%20and%20united%20Palestinian%20leadership%2C%20but%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20policy%2C%20especially%20during%20the%20five%20terms%20of%20Netanyahu%20as%20prime%20minister%2C%20has%20always%20been%20divide%20and%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhenever%20the%20Palestinians%20managed%20to%20reconcile%20their%20differences%2C%20to%20form%20a%20national%20unity%20government%2C%20which%20included%20Hamas%20and%20Fatah%2C%20Israel%20launched%20an%20operation%20which%20disrupted%20the%20national%20unity%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%20by%20its%20actions%20has%20shown%20that%20it%20is%20not%20interested%20in%20having%20a%20Palestinian%20partner%20for%20peace%20because%20it%20wants%20to%20maintain%20its%20control%20over%20the%20territory.%20In%202005%2C%20Israel%20withdrew%20unilaterally%20from%20Gaza%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20for%20its%20own%20reasons%2C%20not%20part%20of%20an%20overall%20settlement%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisrael-asks-india-to-declare-hamas-as-a-terrorist-organisation%5C%22%3EIsrael%20Asks%20India%20to%20Declare%20Hamas%20as%20a%20Terrorist%20Organisation%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20I%20pause%20you%20there%20Professor%20Shlaim%3F%20We%E2%80%99re%20going%20into%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20story%2C%20which%20is%20another%20very%20important%20chapter%2C%20but%20there%20are%20some%20details%20which%20my%20audience%20may%20not%20be%20aware%20of.%20So%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20go%20to%20the%20beginning%20of%20that%2C%20so%20it%20helps%20an%20Indian%20audience%2C%20who%E2%80%99s%20unfamiliar%20with%20it%2C%20understand.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHamas%20was%20founded%20in%201987%20as%20an%20organisation%20committed%20to%20the%20physical%20elimination%20of%20Israel.%20Before%20we%20go%20further%2C%20how%20would%20you%20characterise%20or%20describe%20Hamas%3F%20And%20how%20would%20you%20explain%20its%20ideology%2C%20in%20particular%20the%20goals%20and%20principles%20it%20stands%20for%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EHamas%20is%20an%20Islamic%20resistance%20movement%2C%20and%20Hamas%20emerged%20in%201987%20during%20the%20First%20Palestinian%20Intifada%20or%20uprising%2C%20and%20curiously%2C%20in%20the%20beginning%2C%20Israel%20supported%20Hamas%20as%20a%20counterweight%20to%20the%20secular%20nationalism%20of%20the%20PLO%2C%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20national%20movement.%20So%2C%20Israel%20had%20already%20begun%20to%20play%20the%20game%20of%20divide%20and%20rule%2C%20but%20Hamas%20is%20an%20Islamic%20resistance%20movement%20to%20the%20Israeli%20occupation%2C%20and%20in%202006%2C%20it%20won%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20election.%20It%20won%20an%20absolute%20majority%20in%20an%20all-Palestine%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3EBefore%20we%20go%20into%20that%20detail%2C%20I%20noticed%20that%20you%20described%20Hamas%20very%20carefully%20as%20an%20Islamic%20resistance%20movement%20to%20the%20Israeli%20occupation.%20Many%20people%20today%20insist%20upon%20calling%20Hamas%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%2C%20but%20you%20did%20not.%20Is%20it%20%5Ba%20terrorist%20organisation%3F%5D%20Or%20has%20it%20become%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20since%20its%20foundation%3F%20Or%20is%20that%20only%20partly%20correct%20or%20is%20it%20incorrect%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EIt%20is%20necessary%20to%20distinguish%20between%20the%20political%20leadership%20of%20Hamas%20which%20most%20certainly%20is%20not%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20political%20leadership%20that%20adopted%20the%20parliamentary%20road%20to%20power%20and%20won%20the%20election%20in%20January%202006.%20But%20Hamas%20also%20has%20a%20military%20wing%2C%20and%20the%20military%20wing%20has%20committed%20terrorist%20acts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMost%20recently%20on%20October%207%2C%20it%20launched%20an%20attack%20inside%20Israel%2C%20which%20involved%20a%20massacre%20of%20Israeli%20civilians.%20Attacking%20civilians%20is%20wrong%2C%20killing%20civilians%20is%20wrong%2C%20period.%20There%20can%20be%20no%20debate%20about%20it.%20Whether%20Hamas%20kills%20Israeli%20civilians%2C%20that%20is%20wrong%2C%20and%20if%20Israel%20kills%20Palestinian%20civilians%2C%20as%20it%20is%20doing%20today%20in%20Gaza%2C%20that%20is%20equally%20wrong%2C%20and%20I%20would%20denounce%20it%20as%20state%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20you%E2%80%99re%20making%20a%20distinction%20between%20the%20political%20wing%20of%20Hamas%20and%20the%20military%20wing.%20The%20political%20wing%20%E2%80%93%20as%20you%20were%20saying%20and%20we%E2%80%99ll%20talk%20about%20it%20further%20in%20detail%20%E2%80%93%20won%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20election%20in%202006%20and%20came%20to%20power.%20But%20the%20military%20wing%20has%20been%20indulging%20from%20time%20to%20time%20in%20terrorist%20acts.%20So%20is%20the%20military%20wing%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20military%20wing%20is%20the%20element%20of%20a%20political%20movement%20of%20a%20political%20party%20and%20that%20military%20wing%20has%20committed%20terrorist%20acts%20in%20the%20past%2C%20but%20I%20am%20reluctant%20to%20describe%20it%20as%20a%20terrorist%20organisation.%20I%20would%20like%20to%20examine%20its%20actions%20case%20by%20case%2C%20and%20conclude%20that%20if%20it%20attacks%20civilians%2C%20then%20that%20is%20a%20terrorist%20act%2C%20but%20if%20it%20attacks%20Israeli%20military%20targets%20or%20Israeli%20soldiers%2C%20then%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20call%20it%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20contrary%2C%20I%20would%20say%20that%20people%20under%20occupation%20have%20the%20right%20to%20resist%20under%20international%20law%2C%20and%20Hamas%20is%20exercising%20the%20right%20to%20resist%20the%20Israeli%20occupation%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20only%20element%20within%20the%20Palestinian%20community%20that%20is%20resisting%20the%20occupation%20because%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20in%20Ramallah%20is%20a%20collaborationist%20body.%20It%20collaborates%20with%20Israel%20in%20perpetuating%20the%20occupation.%20So%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20is%20a%20subcontractor%20for%20Israeli%20security%20on%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20which%20is%20why%20it%20has%20lost%20legitimacy%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3A%20In%202006%20January%2C%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20were%20held%20both%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza%2C%20and%20Hamas%20unexpectedly%20won%20a%20decisive%20victory%20over%20Fatah%2C%20but%20when%20Hamas%20formed%20the%20government%2C%20Israel%20refused%20to%20recognise%20it%2C%20and%20the%20United%20States%20and%20the%20European%20Union%20did%20the%20same.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20in%20November%202007%2C%20when%20Fatah%20and%20Hamas%20formed%20a%20government%20of%20national%20unity%20overcoming%20their%20differences%20and%20getting%20together%2C%20you%20are%20saying%20Israel%20and%20the%20US%20plotted%20to%20undermine%20it.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWas%20this%20Israeli%20attitude%20to%20Hamas%20justified%20by%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%201987%20position%20of%20wanting%20to%20eliminate%20Israel%3F%20Or%20was%20Hamas%20changing%20its%20attitude%3F%20And%20did%20Israel%20fail%20to%20realise%20the%20change%2C%20and%20thus%20miss%20another%20opportunity%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EPolitical%20movements%20and%20movements%20on%20national%20liberation%20evolve%20just%20as%20the%20PLO%20evolved%20from%20an%20absolute%20rejection%20of%20Israel%20to%20a%20much%20more%20moderate%20position%20that%20culminated%20in%20signing%20the%20Oslo%20Accord%20with%20Israel.%20Hamas%20is%20a%20political%20movement%20which%20has%20moderated%20its%20position%20since%20the%20Charter%20of%201988%2C%20which%20is%20a%20very%20dogmatic%20and%20even%20anti-semitic%20document%2C%20but%20once%20it%20was%20elected%2C%20Hamas%20seriously%20moderated%20its%20position.%20It%20formed%20a%20coalition%20government%20with%20Fatah%2C%20the%20government%20called%20for%20negotiations%20with%20Israel%20for%20a%20long-term%20ceasefire.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%20refused%20to%20recognise%20the%20Hamas-made%20government%20and%20it%20engaged%20in%20economic%20warfare%20to%20break%20it%20down.%20The%20United%20States%20and%20European%20Union%2C%20to%20their%20shame%2C%20supported%20Israel%20in%20this%20effort%20to%20work%20with%20the%20Hamas-led%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20Western%20powers%20claim%20that%20they%E2%80%99re%20there%20to%20promote%20democracy%2C%20and%20what%20happened%20there%20shows%20how%20hypocritical%20they%20were%2C%20because%20they%20say%20they%20want%20to%20promote%20democracy%20but%20when%20the%20Palestinians%20chose%20the%20wrong%20bunch%20of%20people%20they%20turned%20against%20Hamas%2C%20and%20there%20was%20indeed%20a%20plot%20which%20involved%20Israel%2C%20America%2C%20Fatah%20and%20Egyptian%20intelligence%2C%20to%20isolate%20Hamas%2C%20to%20weaken%20it%2C%20and%20eventually%20to%20overthrow%20it.%20There%20was%20a%20plan%20to%20carry%20out%20a%20coup%20to%20drive%20Hamas%20out%20of%20power%2C%20and%20this%20led%20Hamas%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20violent%20seizure%20of%20power%20in%20Gaza%20in%202007.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20I%20pause%20you%20there%20for%20a%20moment%20Professor%20Shlaim%3F%20Why%20did%20Israel%20take%20this%20attitude%20to%20Hamas%3F%20Was%20it%20because%20Israel%20failed%20to%20realise%20that%20Hamas%20had%20evolved%3F%20That%20is%2C%20Israel%20was%20ignorant%20of%20the%20change%20and%20evolution%20taking%20place%2C%20or%20did%20it%20simply%20turn%20a%20blind%20eye%20and%20refuse%20to%20accept%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EIsrael%20refuses%20to%20accept%20Hamas%20as%20a%20negotiating%20partner.%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20position%20is%20that%20Hamas%20is%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20%E2%80%93%20pure%20and%20simple.%20It%20will%20never%20negotiate%20with%20it.%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20policy%20has%20been%20to%20let%20Hamas%20rule%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20but%20to%20contain%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20and%20this%20policy%20collapsed%2C%20because%20Gaza%20could%20not%20be%20contained.%20What%20Israel%20refuses%20to%20do%20is%20to%20accept%20that%20Hamas%20represents%20a%20serious%20body%20of%20Palestinians%20and%20that%20you%20cannot%20reach%20any%20peace%20agreement%20with%20the%20Palestinians%20that%20excludes%20Hamas.%20So%2C%20the%20sensible%20thing%20for%20Israel%20to%20do%20and%20the%20other%20European%20powers%20to%20do%20is%20to%20recognise%20Hamas%20and%20negotiate%20with%20Hamas%20for%20a%20political%20settlement%20of%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-in-a-gaza-hospital-no-power-lack-of-medicines-many-operations-happening-without-anesthesia%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EWatch%20%7C%20In%20a%20Gaza%20Hospital%2C%20No%20Power%2C%20Lack%20of%20Medicines%2C%20Many%20Operations%20Happening%20Without%20Anesthesia%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%20you%20write%20that%20to%20preempt%20the%20coup%20of%20the%20plot%20which%20you%20were%20talking%20about%20a%20moment%20ago%2C%20one%20in%20which%20Egyptian%20intelligence%2C%20Israel%2C%20the%20United%20States%20were%20all%20involved%2C%20Hamas%20violently%20seized%20power%20in%20Gaza%20in%202007.%20That%20not%20only%20divided%20the%20Palestinian%20movement%20between%20Fatah%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Hamas%20in%20Gaza%2C%20but%20it%20also%20set%20up%20the%20Hamas-Israel%20conflict%20that%E2%80%99s%20virtually%20lasted%20since%20then.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20talk%20about%20that%20conflict.%20Israel%20accuses%20Hamas%20of%20repeated%20terrorist%20attacks%20causing%20Israeli%20deaths.%20Hamas%20accuses%20Israel%20of%20blockading%20the%20Strip%2C%20depriving%20its%20people%20of%20development%2C%20and%20periodic%20air%20strikes%20and%20even%20frequent%20or%20at%20least%20occasional%20ground%20invasions.%20How%20do%20you%2C%20as%20a%20historian%2C%20view%20the%20decade%20and%20a%20half%20since%202007%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EA%20decade%20and%20a%20half%20since%202007%20has%20not%20involved%20any%20movement%2C%20any%20step%20towards%20a%20peaceful%20settlement%20of%20the%20conflict.%20This%20is%20a%20political%20conflict%20between%20the%20two%20sides%2C%20but%20Israel%20only%20uses%20brute%20military%20force%20to%20suppress%20the%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20in%20Gaza%2C%20and%20nothing%20but%20brute%20military%20force.%20There%20is%20an%20Israeli%20saying%20that%2C%20if%20force%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20work%2C%20use%20more%20force%2C%20but%20this%20is%20completely%20ludicrous.%20Military%20force%20cannot%20solve%20the%20political%20dispute%20between%20the%20two%20sides%2C%20and%20Israeli%20generals%20have%20a%20phrase%2C%20%E2%80%98to%20mow%20the%20lawn%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98to%20cut%20the%20grass%2C%E2%80%99%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20horrific%20metaphor%20because%20what%20it%20means%20is%2C%20that%20every%20few%20years%20Israel%20goes%20into%20Gaza%20with%20very%20advanced%20weaponry%2C%20great%20technology%2C%20and%20really%20inflicts%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20damage%2C%20not%20just%20on%20Hamas%20and%20its%20military%20capabilities%2C%20but%20also%20on%20civilians%20and%20the%20civilian%20infrastructure.%20%E2%80%98Mowing%20the%20lawn%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20mechanical%20thing%20that%20you%20do%20every%20now%20and%20again%20to%20set%20back%20Gaza%2C%20and%20there%20is%20no%20light%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20tunnel.%20So%2C%20what%20Israel%20needs%20to%20do%20is%20to%20offer%20a%20political%20horizon%20and%20hope%20to%20the%20Palestinians%20of%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20attitude%20to%20the%20Palestinians%20over%20the%20last%20decade%20or%20so%2C%20you%20write%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20you%2C%20%E2%80%9CIsrael%E2%80%99s%20propaganda%20machine%20persistently%20pervades%20the%20notion%20that%20the%20Palestinians%20are%20terrorists%2C%20that%20they%20reject%20coexistence%20with%20the%20Jewish%20state%2C%20that%20their%20nationalism%20is%20little%20more%20than%20anti-Semitism%2C%20that%20Hamas%20is%20just%20a%20bunch%20of%20religious%20fanatics%2C%20and%20that%20Islam%20is%20incompatible%20with%20democracy.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20you%20suggesting%20that%20this%20is%20not%20just%20deliberate%20misrepresentation%20but%20pretty%20close%20to%20an%20outright%20lie%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EOf%20course%2C%20because%20this%20is%20Israeli%20propaganda.%20It%E2%80%99s%20completely%20one-sided%2C%20and%20it%20completely%20ignores%20what%20we%20have%20talked%20about%20before%2C%20that%20Hamas%20chose%20the%20parliamentary%20road%20to%20power.%20Hamas%20tried%20a%20political%20avenue%20and%20every%20avenue%20that%20the%20Palestinians%20explore%20is%20blocked%20by%20Israel%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20very%20easy%20for%20Israel%20to%20dismiss%20any%20action%20by%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20terrorist%20action%2C%20anything%20by%20Palestinians%2C%20but%20the%20truth%20of%20the%20matter%20is%20that%20the%20Palestinians%20are%20a%20normal%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20want%20what%20every%20normal%20person%20wants%2C%20which%20is%20to%20live%20in%20freedom%20and%20dignity%20on%20their%20own%20land%2C%20and%20it%20is%20Israel%20which%20is%20preventing%20them%20from%20doing%20that.%20Moreover%2C%20Israel%20has%20launched%20successive%20attacks%20on%20Gaza%2C%20the%20first%20one%20was%20Operation%20Cast%20Lead%20in%202008.%20By%20my%20count%2C%20the%20current%20round%20of%20violence%20is%20the%20sixth%20Israeli%20assault%20on%20the%20people%20of%20Gaza%2C%20and%20all%20Israel%20has%20to%20offer%20is%20more%20force%20and%20demonisation%20of%20the%20Palestinians.%20Israel%20systematically%20demonises%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20all%20Palestinians%20as%20terrorists%2C%20and%20the%20danger%20of%20dehumanising%20a%20whole%20people%20is%20that%20it%20paves%20the%20way%20to%20ethnic%20cleansing%20and%20genocide.%20What%20we%20are%20witnessing%20today%2C%20day%20after%20day%2C%20in%20Gaza%20is%20Israel%20moving%20towards%20ethnic%20cleansing%20of%20the%20population%20and%20genocide.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20%3Cstrong%3ENow%20you%20have%20made%20another%20very%20important%20point%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20you%20here%3A%20%E2%80%9CIsrael%20claimed%20to%20be%20the%20victim%20of%20Palestinian%20violence.%E2%80%9D%20The%20truth%20you%20pointed%20out%20is%20very%20different.%20You%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20conflict%20between%20David%20and%20Goliath%2C%20but%20the%20biblical%20image%20was%20inverted.%20A%20small%20and%20defenceless%20Palestinian%20David%20faced%20a%20heavily%20armed%2C%20merciless%2C%20and%20overpowering%20Israeli%20Goliath.%E2%80%9D%20I%20have%20to%20tell%20you%2C%20when%20I%20read%20that%20sentence%2C%20I%20said%20to%20myself%2C%20this%20is%20definitely%20not%20how%20the%20West%20views%20the%20problem.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20opposite%20of%20the%20Western%20perception.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20Western%20perception%20of%20the%20conflict%20is%20completely%20out%20of%20touch%20with%20reality%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20obvious%20to%20anyone%20who%20has%20eyes%2C%20to%20see%20that%20the%20victims%20in%20this%20conflict%20are%20not%20the%20Israelis%2C%20but%20they%20are%20the%20Palestinians.%20This%20is%20indeed%20a%20conflict%20between%20a%20Palestinian%20David%20and%20a%20heavily%20armed%20and%20overbearing%20Israeli%20Goliath%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20asymmetry%20of%20power%20between%20the%20Palestinians%20and%20the%20Israelis%20that%20militates%20against%20a%20peaceful%20solution%20to%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20West%20bears%20a%20large%20share%20of%20the%20responsibility%20for%20the%20impasse%20between%20Israelis%20and%20the%20Palestinians%20because%20the%20West%20is%20completely%20one-sided%20in%20its%20support%20for%20Israel.%20America%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20gives%20Israel%20money%20and%20arms%2C%20and%20diplomatic%20protection.%20The%20trouble%20with%20American%20support%20for%20Israel%20is%20that%20it%20is%20unconditional%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20conditional%20on%20Israel%20obeying%20international%20law%2C%20or%20respecting%20Palestinian%20human%20rights.%20It%E2%80%99s%20this%20unconditional%20American%2C%20and%20British%2C%20and%20largely%20European%20Union%20support%20for%20Israel%20which%20enables%20Israel%20to%20get%20away%2C%20literally%20with%20murder.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20saw%20during%20this%20crisis%20that%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20Rishi%20Sunak%20and%20other%20European%20leaders%20rushed%20to%20Israel%20to%20visit%2C%20to%20show%20their%20support%20for%20Israel%2C%20but%20they%20haven%E2%80%99t%20called%20for%20a%20ceasefire.%20Surely%2C%20the%20decent%20thing%20to%20do%20in%20the%20present%20situation%20is%20to%20call%20for%20a%20ceasefire%2C%20and%20Hamas%20has%20offered%20to%20release%20the%20civilian%20hostages%20in%20return%20for%20a%20ceasefire%2C%20but%20it%20is%20Israel%20that%20is%20refusing%20to%20stop%20its%20bombardment%20of%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fde-escalation-ceasefire-among-phrases-to-avoid-in-press-materials-show-us-state-dept-emails%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98De-escalation%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98Ceasefire%E2%80%99%20Among%20Phrases%20to%20Avoid%20in%20Press%20Materials%2C%20Show%20Us%20State%20Dept%20Emails%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%2C%20it%20was%20against%20this%20background%20which%20we%E2%80%99ve%20discussed%20in%20some%20detail%2C%20that%20Hamas%20launched%20its%20October%207%20attack.%20Does%20the%20history%20that%20we%E2%80%99ve%20discussed%20explain%20why%20that%20attack%20happened%3F%20Even%20if%20it%20certainly%20cannot%20justify%20it%20or%20even%20excuse%20it.%20And%20I%E2%80%99m%20making%20that%20clear%20to%20the%20audience%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20that%20the%20history%20justifies%20or%20excuses%20the%20attack%2C%20but%20does%20it%20explain%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20October%207%20attack%20by%20Hamas%20in%20Israel%20has%20attracted%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20denunciation%20for%20a%20very%20good%20reason%2C%20because%20it%20was%20an%20attack%20on%20civilians.%20So%2C%20I%20denounce%20the%20Hamas%20attack%20on%20Israeli%20civilians%20inside%20Israel%2C%20and%20much%20of%20the%20commentary%20speaks%20about%20October%207%20as%20a%20barbaric%20attack.%20What%20many%20commentators%20forget%20is%20that%20the%20conflict%20did%20not%20start%20on%20October%207.%20The%20conflict%20has%20to%20be%20seen%20against%2056%20years%20of%20Israeli%20occupation%2C%20since%201967.%20The%20Israeli%20occupation%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20lands%20is%20a%20daily%20violence%20against%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20and%20when%20Israel%20withdrew%20from%20Gaza%20unilaterally%20in%202005%2C%20it%20effectively%20turned%20Gaza%20into%20a%20prison%2C%20into%20the%20biggest%20open-air%20prison%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20it%20imposed%20a%20blockade%2C%20already%20in%202007%2C%20a%20blockade%20of%20Gaza%20which%20is%20illegal%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20form%20of%20collective%20punishment.%20Now%20since%20October%207%2C%20Israel%20has%20intensified%20the%20blockade%20and%20committed%20war%20crimes%20by%20cutting%20off%20water%2C%20food%2C%20electricity%2C%20fuel%2C%20and%20medical%20supplies%20to%20the%20population%20of%20Gaza.%20So%2C%20the%20conflict%20didn%E2%80%99t%20start%20on%20October%207%20and%20the%20action%20by%20Hamas%20has%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20an%20act%20of%20resistance%20to%20the%20Israeli%20occupation%2C%20and%20the%20history%20that%20we%20have%20reviewed%20briefly%20in%20our%20conversation.%20It%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20justify%20the%20attack%20of%20Hamas%20on%20October%207%2C%20but%20it%20surely%20gives%20the%20backdrop%20to%20what%20has%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%20tries%20to%20contain%20the%20prison%20and%20now%20the%20prisoners%20have%20broken%20out%20of%20the%20prison.%20There%20is%20a%20Jewish-American%20writer%2C%20named%20Norman%20Finkelstein%2C%20who%20has%20described%20this%20as%20the%20revolt%20of%20the%20slaves.%20It%E2%80%99s%20the%20underdogs%20who%20have%20taken%20the%20initiative%20in%20breaking%20the%20siege.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3A%20A%20sort%20of%20modern-day%20Spartacus.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EIndeed%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20quite%20an%20interesting%20historical%20comparison%2C%20absolutely.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwearing-bracelets-to-avoid-a-mass-grave-a-palestinian-icon-bears-witness%5C%22%3EWearing%20Bracelets%20to%20Avoid%20a%20Mass%20Grave%3A%20A%20Palestinian%20Icon%20Bears%20Witness%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20%3Cstrong%3EIn%20your%20writing%2C%20you%20make%20three%20broad%20thematic%20points%20about%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20conflict.%20First%2C%20you%20say%2C%20Israelis%20regard%20themselves%20as%20victims%2C%20but%20then%20you%20tellingly%20add%2C%20%5Bthat%20they%5D%20feeling%20themselves%20to%20be%20the%20victims%20tends%20to%20blind%20the%20Israeli%20majority%20to%20the%20suffering%20they%20inflict%20on%20the%20real%20victims%20in%20this%20conflict%2C%20the%20Palestinians.%20Are%20you%20saying%20that%20Israelis%20are%20oblivious%20to%2C%20or%20at%20least%2C%20blind%20to%20the%20sufferings%20they%20have%20inflicted%20on%20the%20Palestinians%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProfessor%20Shlaim%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EYes%2C%20and%20the%20Israeli%20media%20is%20a%20loyalist%20media%20that%20follows%20the%20party%20line%2C%20the%20government%20line%2C%20and%20there%20is%20very%20little%20reporting%20of%20what%20happens%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20hill%2C%20what%20happens%20in%20the%20occupied%20territories.%20So%2C%20Israelis%20are%20largely%20ignorant%20of%20what%20happens%20on%20the%20other%20side%2C%20and%20they%20also%20have%20a%20tendency%20to%20see%20themselves%20as%20victims.%20History%20explains%20why%20this%20should%20be%20so%2C%20the%20Jews%20have%20suffered%20a%20great%20deal%2C%20and%20the%20Jews%20endured%20the%20Holocaust%2C%20the%20Holocaust%20explains%20why%20Israelis%20are%20so%20obsessed%2C%20so%20concerned%2C%20almost%20obsessed%20with%20security%2C%20but%20this%20acute%20preoccupation%20with%20Israeli%20security%20does%20blind%20Israelis%20to%20the%20insecurity%20of%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%20demands%20100%25%20security%20for%20itself.%20This%20translates%20into%20100%25%20insecurity%20for%20the%20Palestinians%20as%20we%E2%80%99re%20witnessing%20today%20in%20Gaza%2C%20so%20yes%2C%20the%20Israeli%20public%20is%20not%20well-informed%20about%20the%20rights%20and%20wrongs%2C%20or%20about%20the%20history%20of%20this%20conflict%2C%20and%20its%20leadership%2C%20especially%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%5Bwho%5D%20plays%20a%20major%20role%20in%20misinforming%20the%20public%20about%20the%20reality%20of%20the%20situation%20and%20about%20the%20legitimate%20rights%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20